1
00:00:16,359 --> 00:00:18,644
[Today]
Hey, can you ride a bike?

2
00:00:18,644 --> 00:00:21,347
[The last day of their anniversary trip]
It'd be so nice if all four of us went biking.

3
00:00:21,347 --> 00:00:23,526
I've always wanted to play yut on the porch.

4
00:00:23,526 --> 00:00:25,284
Where can we get stuffed squid?

5
00:00:25,284 --> 00:00:27,393
The four of us have never

6
00:00:27,393 --> 00:00:29,555
- just gone outside and played around.
- Yeah, exactly.

7
00:00:29,555 --> 00:00:31,123
[A bucket list saved for this very day]
Oh, what's that over there?

8
00:00:31,123 --> 00:00:33,493
- This is so much fun!
- This is awesome!

9
00:00:33,493 --> 00:00:34,860
- Mo! Got you!
- What?

10
00:00:34,860 --> 00:00:35,728
I rolled Mo!

11
00:00:35,728 --> 00:00:38,164
- You're the mo queen.
- Seriously.

12
00:00:38,164 --> 00:00:40,766
You're seriously so moody.

13
00:00:40,766 --> 00:00:42,992
You're actually getting on my nerves.

14
00:00:42,992 --> 00:00:45,404
[Meanwhile, the victory dance continues]
Eun Tak.

15
00:00:45,404 --> 00:00:49,341
<i>♪ Goblin's underwear is nice and strong ♪</i>

16
00:00:51,377 --> 00:00:53,126
[A treat for Goblin fans]

17
00:00:53,126 --> 00:00:55,593
[The four give it their all on the final day]
Make a heart.

18
00:00:55,593 --> 00:00:58,317
Big smiles. Hi!

19
00:00:59,352 --> 00:01:03,556
[EP. 4 Every Moment With You Was Dazzling]

20
00:01:03,556 --> 00:01:07,593
[After a night worth remembering]

21
00:01:07,593 --> 00:01:11,130
[A new day dawns]

22
00:01:11,130 --> 00:01:15,968
[Ready for a brand-new page to be written]

23
00:01:15,968 --> 00:01:17,870
[Blue skies and endless sea]

24
00:01:17,870 --> 00:01:20,673
[With the waves rolling in]

25
00:01:23,309 --> 00:01:27,246
[Goblin House wakes to a dazzling morning]

26
00:01:30,460 --> 00:01:31,984
Good morning.

27
00:01:31,984 --> 00:01:35,221
[Dong Wook and In Na are up early]

28
00:01:35,221 --> 00:01:36,359
Another beautiful day.

29
00:01:36,359 --> 00:01:38,124
Yeah.

30
00:01:38,124 --> 00:01:39,859
Oh, we forgot to put away the charcoal bin!

31
00:01:39,859 --> 00:01:41,928
- Which one?
- The charcoal bin.

32
00:01:41,928 --> 00:01:43,195
- That one?
- Yeah.

33
00:01:43,195 --> 00:01:45,664
We kept the charcoal going for three hours.

34
00:01:46,632 --> 00:01:49,969
Goblin kept stressing over it the whole time.

35
00:01:49,969 --> 00:01:51,304
Yesterday...

36
00:01:51,304 --> 00:01:53,839
feels like a dream now.

37
00:01:53,839 --> 00:01:56,475
- It's kind of surreal, right?
- Yeah.

38
00:01:56,475 --> 00:01:58,793
Doesn't looking at the ocean clear your head?

39
00:01:58,793 --> 00:02:01,881
I want to live here.

40
00:02:01,881 --> 00:02:04,984
[Front-row seats to the ocean]

41
00:02:04,984 --> 00:02:09,026
[The whole ocean right outside]

42
00:02:09,026 --> 00:02:10,964
I want to live here.

43
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:13,726
[And there goes the mood]
No, you couldn't actually live here.

44
00:02:13,726 --> 00:02:14,760
Oh, come on.

45
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,529
You'd start whining
about how inconvenient it is.

46
00:02:16,529 --> 00:02:18,230
True.

47
00:02:18,230 --> 00:02:20,593
[So much for the romance]

48
00:02:20,593 --> 00:02:23,436
Do you have any cash on you?

49
00:02:23,436 --> 00:02:25,404
- Cash? Right now?
- Yeah, right now.

50
00:02:25,404 --> 00:02:27,399
[A sudden wallet check]
No, I only have my card. Why?

51
00:02:27,399 --> 00:02:29,860
I have a card too.

52
00:02:29,860 --> 00:02:34,013
I'm trying to decide
whether I should buy you coffee.

53
00:02:34,013 --> 00:02:35,848
[Morning coffee sounds good!]
There's a café around here?

54
00:02:35,848 --> 00:02:38,159
I got up early, remember? I found one.

55
00:02:38,159 --> 00:02:39,885
How did you already find a café?

56
00:02:39,885 --> 00:02:41,387
- So then...
- Yeah?

57
00:02:41,387 --> 00:02:43,055
Wait here for a second.

58
00:02:43,055 --> 00:02:44,359
I'll come with you.

59
00:02:44,359 --> 00:02:45,925
Okay, fine.

60
00:02:45,925 --> 00:02:47,126
[Sneaking in]

61
00:02:47,126 --> 00:02:48,593
Where are we going?

62
00:02:48,593 --> 00:02:51,664
- No, keep looking at the ocean over there.
- Okay.

63
00:02:51,664 --> 00:02:54,567
[A carefully planned approach]

64
00:02:54,567 --> 00:02:57,036
[Hee-hee!]
What is this?

65
00:02:57,036 --> 00:02:59,259
[Dong Wook gets a cute makeover]
You can only come if you wear this.

66
00:02:59,259 --> 00:03:01,359
- What is it?
- That's the deal.

67
00:03:01,359 --> 00:03:03,975
This looks like a camera cover.

68
00:03:04,726 --> 00:03:06,045
No, you have to wear it.

69
00:03:06,045 --> 00:03:07,359
- No, I'm good.
- No.

70
00:03:07,359 --> 00:03:09,448
You have to wear it
if you want me to buy the coffee.

71
00:03:09,448 --> 00:03:10,149
Forget it.

72
00:03:10,149 --> 00:03:12,718
- No, I...
- I'm telling you, it's a camera cover.

73
00:03:12,718 --> 00:03:15,226
No, it's not. I brought it from home.

74
00:03:15,226 --> 00:03:16,522
- Really?
- Yes.

75
00:03:16,522 --> 00:03:17,523
- What is this, then?
- This...

76
00:03:17,523 --> 00:03:20,325
[Yoo In Na bought the Grim Reaper's hat]
It's the hat you wore in Guardian.

77
00:03:22,762 --> 00:03:24,326
I'm going to smash it.

78
00:03:24,326 --> 00:03:30,069
[Goblin's prank on the sleeping Grim Reaper]

79
00:03:30,069 --> 00:03:31,326
[In Na came prepared with a throwback]

80
00:03:31,326 --> 00:03:32,760
- When you turned into a baby...
- Yeah.

81
00:03:32,760 --> 00:03:35,374
- So...
- That's what I used when I was washing up.

82
00:03:35,374 --> 00:03:36,642
- Let's go.
- No, I'm good.

83
00:03:36,642 --> 00:03:39,428
- Okay, enough with the joke.
- Let's go.

84
00:03:39,428 --> 00:03:40,446
It's not a joke.

85
00:03:40,446 --> 00:03:41,660
- No!
- I'm good.

86
00:03:41,660 --> 00:03:43,182
I said you have to.

87
00:03:43,182 --> 00:03:46,052
- You have to wear this before we go.
- I did. That's enough. Let's go already.

88
00:03:46,052 --> 00:03:48,154
- You never listen.
- Where are we going?

89
00:03:48,154 --> 00:03:50,523
- Why won't you wear it?
- So where are we going?

90
00:03:50,523 --> 00:03:51,827
We're going to a café.

91
00:03:51,827 --> 00:03:53,159
Where's the café?

92
00:03:53,159 --> 00:03:54,326
Don't we need the GPS?

93
00:03:54,326 --> 00:03:56,359
[In Na gives up and heads to the café]

94
00:03:56,359 --> 00:03:57,530
Which way?

95
00:03:57,530 --> 00:03:58,698
Left.

96
00:03:58,698 --> 00:04:00,366
- Oh, this way?
- Yeah.

97
00:04:00,366 --> 00:04:02,193
- What's over this way?
- I bought that just for you.

98
00:04:02,193 --> 00:04:04,436
[Still not letting it go]
Why won't you wear it?

99
00:04:06,072 --> 00:04:08,874
[Their bickering wakes Gong Yoo]

100
00:04:08,874 --> 00:04:11,959
[Where are those two going?]

101
00:04:11,959 --> 00:04:15,347
[I'm right here...]

102
00:04:15,347 --> 00:04:19,185
[Half awake, half asleep]

103
00:04:19,185 --> 00:04:22,043
[Straight to the kitchen after waking up]

104
00:04:25,024 --> 00:04:28,394
[First, he checks the fridge]

105
00:04:28,394 --> 00:04:31,797
[After a quiet kitchen check]

106
00:04:31,797 --> 00:04:35,059
[He tidies up the house too]

107
00:04:35,059 --> 00:04:37,036
- Have you been back here before?
- When did you come around this way?

108
00:04:37,036 --> 00:04:41,240
I figured I'd take a lap and look for a café,
and there actually was one.

109
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:44,193
- Hello.
- Hello.

110
00:04:44,193 --> 00:04:45,678
What are you getting?

111
00:04:45,678 --> 00:04:47,713
If I get something like an Einspänner,

112
00:04:47,713 --> 00:04:49,448
will I look cool?

113
00:04:51,593 --> 00:04:54,760
[Trying to look like a coffee expert]
Will I look like I know my coffee?

114
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:56,992
[Going with the fancy one]
Then let's try the Einspänner.

115
00:04:56,992 --> 00:04:59,393
- The other two will want Americanos, right?
- Yeah.

116
00:04:59,393 --> 00:05:01,761
[In Na treats everyone to coffee]
Two iced Americanos, please.

117
00:05:01,761 --> 00:05:04,449
And a lemonade for me, please.

118
00:05:05,226 --> 00:05:07,566
- They've got all kinds of stuff in here.
- Why? Do you want something?

119
00:05:07,566 --> 00:05:09,769
No. I'm just looking.

120
00:05:09,769 --> 00:05:12,860
[She joins him for a look]

121
00:05:12,860 --> 00:05:14,774
How do I look?

122
00:05:14,774 --> 00:05:16,860
[Waiting for a compliment]

123
00:05:16,860 --> 00:05:19,144
You look like someone carrying that bag.

124
00:05:20,479 --> 00:05:23,626
[Not the answer she wanted]
I just look like someone carrying this bag?

125
00:05:23,626 --> 00:05:25,193
Yeah. It looks easy to carry. Nice and light.

126
00:05:25,193 --> 00:05:26,359
- Really?
- Yeah.

127
00:05:26,359 --> 00:05:29,088
Then the woman carrying this bag...

128
00:05:29,088 --> 00:05:31,657
and the woman carrying this one?

129
00:05:31,657 --> 00:05:33,325
[Suddenly, it's a test]

130
00:05:33,325 --> 00:05:35,528
Which one do you like better?

131
00:05:35,528 --> 00:05:37,229
This woman...

132
00:05:37,229 --> 00:05:39,259
[Still focused on the bags]

133
00:05:39,259 --> 00:05:40,399
or this woman?

134
00:05:40,399 --> 00:05:42,008
- Don't just look at the bags.
- I think this one's better.

135
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,303
Look at the whole outfit.

136
00:05:45,137 --> 00:05:46,238
Which one did you say was better?

137
00:05:46,238 --> 00:05:48,908
- Okay, look at the whole look.
- Okay, got it. Do it again.

138
00:05:48,908 --> 00:05:50,593
[Option 1]
[An impromptu fashion show]

139
00:05:50,593 --> 00:05:52,278
- This woman...
- Okay.

140
00:05:52,278 --> 00:05:54,013
[Focused]

141
00:05:54,013 --> 00:05:56,081
[Option 2]

142
00:05:56,081 --> 00:05:59,393
- The second woman looks like she's in a hurry!
- She is.

143
00:05:59,393 --> 00:06:02,087
Okay, then see what you think of this woman.

144
00:06:02,087 --> 00:06:03,923
[Licking his dry lips]

145
00:06:03,923 --> 00:06:07,893
[And now, Option 3]

146
00:06:07,893 --> 00:06:09,562
Which of the three?

147
00:06:09,562 --> 00:06:13,064
The third one looked the worst.

148
00:06:15,259 --> 00:06:17,269
[Dong Wook's brutally honest answer]
Why is she acting so coy?

149
00:06:17,269 --> 00:06:19,193
No, say something nice.

150
00:06:19,193 --> 00:06:21,793
- I asked you to pick the one you liked best.
- The first bag looks best.

151
00:06:21,793 --> 00:06:24,062
- I think the first bag looks the best.
- This one? Okay.

152
00:06:24,062 --> 00:06:25,526
[Her past-life love tries his best...]

153
00:06:25,526 --> 00:06:27,226
- Ready to check out?
- Do you take Apple Pay?

154
00:06:27,226 --> 00:06:28,247
- Yes, of course.
- Great.

155
00:06:28,247 --> 00:06:30,216
- Really?
- Yeah.

156
00:06:30,216 --> 00:06:31,560
[He casually picks up the tab]

157
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,959
So that's why the early bird...

158
00:06:33,959 --> 00:06:35,487
- Gets the bag.
- Exactly.

159
00:06:35,487 --> 00:06:36,927
[The early In Na gets the bag]

160
00:06:36,927 --> 00:06:37,957
This is amazing.

161
00:06:37,957 --> 00:06:39,026
I'll wrap it up for you.

162
00:06:39,026 --> 00:06:40,793
Thank you.

163
00:06:40,793 --> 00:06:42,328
Actually, I'll carry it.

164
00:06:42,328 --> 00:06:43,359
- Would you like to use it right away?
- Yes.

165
00:06:43,359 --> 00:06:44,927
- Then should I just remove the tag?
- Yes, please.

166
00:06:44,927 --> 00:06:48,493
Otherwise, he might make me
return it later if I mess up.

167
00:06:48,493 --> 00:06:49,969
Thank you.

168
00:06:49,969 --> 00:06:51,337
[The Peach Couple starts the day with gifts]

169
00:06:51,337 --> 00:06:52,660
[Walking on air]

170
00:06:52,660 --> 00:06:54,540
How do I look?

171
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:55,593
Don't I look so happy?

172
00:06:55,593 --> 00:06:58,077
- I'm seriously so happy right now.
- Yeah.

173
00:06:58,077 --> 00:07:00,979
You look thrilled about your new bag.

174
00:07:02,927 --> 00:07:05,092
How about we leave this by the door

175
00:07:05,092 --> 00:07:06,418
- and take a quick walk?
- Sure.

176
00:07:06,418 --> 00:07:08,153
- Sounds good, right?
- Yeah.

177
00:07:09,088 --> 00:07:10,660
[Perfect for a walk]

178
00:07:10,660 --> 00:07:13,058
This is so nice.

179
00:07:13,058 --> 00:07:15,293
[A refreshing ocean view]

180
00:07:15,293 --> 00:07:17,229
Wait, let's grab our sunglasses.

181
00:07:17,229 --> 00:07:18,530
- Yeah, good idea.
- Okay.

182
00:07:18,530 --> 00:07:19,860
[First, they drop off the morning coffee]

183
00:07:19,860 --> 00:07:22,500
Where did I put my sunglasses, anyway?

184
00:07:23,326 --> 00:07:25,471
- Wait, what? How do we get in?
- Oh, is it locked?

185
00:07:25,471 --> 00:07:26,839
- The code is 1004.
- 1004.

186
00:07:26,839 --> 00:07:28,259
Right.

187
00:07:28,259 --> 00:07:29,008
Huh?

188
00:07:29,008 --> 00:07:31,126
- Hey.
- Hey.

189
00:07:31,126 --> 00:07:32,378
[Goblin Gong suddenly appears]
1004.

190
00:07:32,378 --> 00:07:34,513
You actually got up!

191
00:07:34,513 --> 00:07:36,649
- Did you sleep well?
- Yeah.

192
00:07:36,649 --> 00:07:38,083
How'd you manage to get up?

193
00:07:38,083 --> 00:07:40,292
I got up just fine.

194
00:07:40,292 --> 00:07:41,893
Is Eun Tak up?

195
00:07:41,893 --> 00:07:43,255
[Right on cue]

196
00:07:43,255 --> 00:07:44,790
- Hi!
- Hi!

197
00:07:44,790 --> 00:07:46,792
Oh, Eun Tak's up.

198
00:07:46,792 --> 00:07:48,394
[The youngest is up too]

199
00:07:48,394 --> 00:07:50,495
Good job, Eun Tak.

200
00:07:51,126 --> 00:07:52,893
For what? Waking up?

201
00:07:52,893 --> 00:07:54,033
Yeah.

202
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:56,635
- Thanks for saying that.
- I didn't think you'd get up today.

203
00:07:56,635 --> 00:07:58,159
[Praised just for waking up]

204
00:07:58,159 --> 00:07:59,927
We went out for coffee, and In Na...

205
00:07:59,927 --> 00:08:01,774
How are you always so sweet?

206
00:08:01,774 --> 00:08:03,992
talked me into buying her a bag.

207
00:08:03,992 --> 00:08:05,711
Huh?

208
00:08:05,711 --> 00:08:06,745
- A bag?
- Yeah.

209
00:08:06,745 --> 00:08:07,696
Where?

210
00:08:07,696 --> 00:08:10,059
They sell bags at that café.

211
00:08:10,059 --> 00:08:11,784
[Showing off the bag]
- What do you think? - Oh! What's that?

212
00:08:11,784 --> 00:08:13,786
Isn't it adorable?

213
00:08:13,786 --> 00:08:15,601
Let me see it.

214
00:08:15,601 --> 00:08:17,026
I went through this whole thing
picking one out,

215
00:08:17,026 --> 00:08:18,791
- It's so cute.
- and bought this one. Cute, right?

216
00:08:18,791 --> 00:08:19,959
[So jealous]

217
00:08:19,959 --> 00:08:21,426
[A playful little pose]

218
00:08:21,426 --> 00:08:23,393
Oh, this...

219
00:08:23,393 --> 00:08:24,793
Does it suit me?

220
00:08:24,793 --> 00:08:26,226
It does.

221
00:08:26,226 --> 00:08:28,367
You look so pretty.

222
00:08:28,367 --> 00:08:30,369
- Want to go for a walk?
- Huh?

223
00:08:30,369 --> 00:08:31,560
Want to take a walk?

224
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,493
No, I have to make breakfast.

225
00:08:33,493 --> 00:08:35,541
Breakfast...

226
00:08:35,541 --> 00:08:39,493
[Goblin always comes back to food]

227
00:08:39,493 --> 00:08:41,013
Do I have to wash my face?

228
00:08:41,013 --> 00:08:44,092
Wash your face? You should wash your face.

229
00:08:44,092 --> 00:08:46,618
- Wash my face...
- We're still going out, right?

230
00:08:46,618 --> 00:08:48,354
What about Eun Tak? Are you washing up?

231
00:08:48,354 --> 00:08:49,288
I have to?

232
00:08:49,288 --> 00:08:51,023
- Yes, you do.
- No, you don't have to.

233
00:08:51,023 --> 00:08:52,958
No, she should.

234
00:08:52,958 --> 00:08:54,226
Come with us.

235
00:08:54,226 --> 00:08:56,226
[You two go ahead]
You're not coming?

236
00:08:56,226 --> 00:08:57,262
Can't be bothered?

237
00:08:57,262 --> 00:08:58,760
[Too tired to wash up or take a walk]

238
00:08:58,760 --> 00:09:01,460
I'll sit here and have some coffee for a bit.

239
00:09:01,460 --> 00:09:03,002
Yeah, go ahead.

240
00:09:03,002 --> 00:09:05,170
Your coffee's here.
You can have some lemonade too.

241
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:07,473
[Leaving them to enjoy a quiet drink]

242
00:09:07,473 --> 00:09:12,644
[The Peach Couple heads out for a walk]

243
00:09:12,644 --> 00:09:15,441
[Have a nice walk]

244
00:09:16,815 --> 00:09:18,359
Still, if we're at the beach...

245
00:09:18,359 --> 00:09:19,651
- This is nice.
- we should hit the sand.

246
00:09:19,651 --> 00:09:21,927
- You're right.
- Yeah.

247
00:09:21,927 --> 00:09:23,560
You feel so familiar to me.

248
00:09:23,560 --> 00:09:24,992
I feel familiar to you too, right?

249
00:09:24,992 --> 00:09:26,792
- Of course you do.
- Right?

250
00:09:26,792 --> 00:09:29,094
I mean, there was Guardian,

251
00:09:29,094 --> 00:09:32,398
- and then we did Touch Your Heart too.
- Exactly.

252
00:09:32,398 --> 00:09:37,436
[As Wang Yeo and Kim Sun in Guardian]

253
00:09:37,436 --> 00:09:39,104
What do you like?

254
00:09:39,104 --> 00:09:40,172
You, Sunny.

255
00:09:40,172 --> 00:09:42,893
[As the Grim Reaper and Sunny]

256
00:09:42,893 --> 00:09:44,043
This is driving me crazy.

257
00:09:44,043 --> 00:09:47,086
I'm Lee Hyuk with Gangnam Homicide.

258
00:09:47,086 --> 00:09:49,748
[Together again in their third lifetime]
Your name is Hyuk. No way.

259
00:09:49,748 --> 00:09:51,917
I can hear you.

260
00:09:51,917 --> 00:09:53,726
[Their story continued in Touch Your Heart]

261
00:09:53,726 --> 00:09:56,088
I like you. I really like you.

262
00:09:56,088 --> 00:09:58,389
Let's date!

263
00:10:00,326 --> 00:10:02,061
[Two shows brought them even closer]

264
00:10:02,061 --> 00:10:04,129
- We got even more comfortable.
- Right.

265
00:10:04,129 --> 00:10:06,498
- Even if it's been a while...
- Yeah.

266
00:10:06,498 --> 00:10:07,959
- It never feels awkward.
- We're like a couple

267
00:10:07,959 --> 00:10:10,201
who were married forever and then divorced.

268
00:10:11,103 --> 00:10:14,126
[Picture-perfect, despite the topic]

269
00:10:14,126 --> 00:10:15,941
So it's not even a love-hate thing?

270
00:10:15,941 --> 00:10:17,743
- No.
- The good and the bad...

271
00:10:17,743 --> 00:10:19,159
Have we moved past all of it?

272
00:10:19,159 --> 00:10:21,213
We've moved way past it.

273
00:10:21,213 --> 00:10:23,693
But if anything ever happened,

274
00:10:23,693 --> 00:10:28,720
[The one they trust most when it counts]
you'd still be the first person I'd side with.

275
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,323
This is so nice.

276
00:10:31,323 --> 00:10:32,860
The others should've come out
and walked with us.

277
00:10:32,860 --> 00:10:34,793
- This is nice.
- Yeah, they should've.

278
00:10:35,494 --> 00:10:37,942
[Family is never far from their minds]
Where'd they go for their walk?

279
00:10:38,693 --> 00:10:40,099
Where are you going now?

280
00:10:40,099 --> 00:10:41,827
[Gomtang]
I was going to heat it up...

281
00:10:41,827 --> 00:10:44,203
Just sit down for a minute.

282
00:10:44,203 --> 00:10:46,839
No, let me at least get this simmering.

283
00:10:46,839 --> 00:10:49,742
[He can't stop thinking about cooking]
How long does it even take to heat up?

284
00:10:49,742 --> 00:10:52,878
- Does it take 10 minutes? 20 minutes?
- No, I need to be doing something.

285
00:10:52,878 --> 00:10:55,848
I'm saying, let's just have this first.

286
00:10:55,848 --> 00:10:58,927
[Chef Gong finally sits back down]
We always have coffee in the morning.

287
00:10:58,927 --> 00:11:02,014
- Coffee break.
- But we haven't eaten anything yet.

288
00:11:03,539 --> 00:11:06,026
[Up again for the third time]
Give me a second.

289
00:11:06,026 --> 00:11:08,226
I'm just sticking to my routine.

290
00:11:08,226 --> 00:11:10,827
[Straight back to the kitchen]
Fine. Go. Then I'll just wash my face.

291
00:11:10,827 --> 00:11:13,290
You haven't even washed your face?

292
00:11:13,290 --> 00:11:15,493
[Nope, not yet...]

293
00:11:15,493 --> 00:11:18,793
- Did you wash up already?
- Of course. I washed my face!

294
00:11:18,793 --> 00:11:20,372
- I should wash my face and put on sunscreen.
- Yeah.

295
00:11:20,372 --> 00:11:21,540
- Hurry up.
- Did you put on sunscreen?

296
00:11:21,540 --> 00:11:22,526
- No.
- Come here.

297
00:11:22,526 --> 00:11:24,475
Okay, give me a second.

298
00:11:25,577 --> 00:11:26,893
[Go Eun grabs Gong Yoo's sunscreen first]

299
00:11:26,893 --> 00:11:29,227
- Come here.
- One second.

300
00:11:32,784 --> 00:11:36,155
[They got married in Guardian]

301
00:11:36,155 --> 00:11:38,426
[After a sweet newlywed phase]
That looks delicious.

302
00:11:38,426 --> 00:11:42,761
<i>♪ I'm happy too ♪</i>

303
00:11:42,761 --> 00:11:47,298
[The Goblin couple still cares for each other]

304
00:11:49,635 --> 00:11:52,004
[Pat, pat, pat]

305
00:11:52,004 --> 00:11:54,226
[Now she washes up]

306
00:11:54,226 --> 00:11:56,426
Look at me.

307
00:11:56,426 --> 00:11:58,210
- Why?
- Is it all rubbed in?

308
00:11:58,210 --> 00:11:59,578
- Huh?
- Is it rubbed in?

309
00:11:59,578 --> 00:12:01,280
Yeah, perfect.

310
00:12:01,280 --> 00:12:02,447
Good job.

311
00:12:02,447 --> 00:12:04,363
[Hehe]

312
00:12:06,318 --> 00:12:08,153
[Chef Gong starts breakfast]

313
00:12:08,153 --> 00:12:10,889
[His hangover cure: spicy yukgaejang]
When did they even get up?

314
00:12:10,889 --> 00:12:13,827
But In Na said she wanted that.

315
00:12:13,827 --> 00:12:15,027
What?

316
00:12:15,027 --> 00:12:17,029
Bigfin squid.

317
00:12:17,029 --> 00:12:18,363
- Oh, the ramen?
- Yeah.

318
00:12:18,363 --> 00:12:20,633
Then I'll make the spicy yukgaejang,

319
00:12:20,633 --> 00:12:23,769
and let's make two packs of bigfin squid ramen.

320
00:12:23,769 --> 00:12:25,259
- I mean...
- We also have that clear gomtang.

321
00:12:25,259 --> 00:12:26,972
Let's skip the gomtang.

322
00:12:26,972 --> 00:12:28,574
The gomtang...

323
00:12:28,574 --> 00:12:29,641
Mix it in.

324
00:12:29,641 --> 00:12:30,959
- Mix it into what?
- The spicy yukgaejang.

325
00:12:30,959 --> 00:12:32,945
- No!
- Yes!

326
00:12:32,945 --> 00:12:34,780
No! They're completely different!

327
00:12:34,780 --> 00:12:37,893
This one is actual gomtang,
and that one is yukgaejang.

328
00:12:37,893 --> 00:12:38,992
- It'll be fine.
- No, I don't want to.

329
00:12:38,992 --> 00:12:40,752
- They have the same base.
- No.

330
00:12:40,752 --> 00:12:42,593
I'm telling you, it's the same base.

331
00:12:42,593 --> 00:12:44,159
No.

332
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:46,425
That's my point.
The yukgaejang starts with this broth.

333
00:12:46,425 --> 00:12:48,594
I know, but then the yukgaejang
won't taste right.

334
00:12:48,594 --> 00:12:50,929
[Bickering over breakfast]
- Why wouldn't it? - You like the spicy one.

335
00:12:50,929 --> 00:12:53,865
- It'll taste even better if we mix them.
- No.

336
00:12:53,865 --> 00:12:54,927
I've tried both.

337
00:12:54,927 --> 00:12:56,401
No, no.

338
00:12:56,401 --> 00:12:57,693
You have so many rules!

339
00:12:57,693 --> 00:12:59,738
It'll end up tasting like neither one.

340
00:12:59,738 --> 00:13:01,526
Sometimes you can do it this way,

341
00:13:01,526 --> 00:13:03,542
- and sometimes another way.
- No.

342
00:13:03,542 --> 00:13:06,378
You only mix things that go together.
Are you serious?

343
00:13:06,378 --> 00:13:09,915
- But yukgaejang and gomtang...
- I'm telling you, it'll taste like neither one.

344
00:13:09,915 --> 00:13:11,493
[A Goblin couple's spat never lasts]
Fine.

345
00:13:11,493 --> 00:13:13,352
Good.

346
00:13:13,352 --> 00:13:15,754
[The Peach Couple returns from their walk]

347
00:13:15,754 --> 00:13:18,626
Look, you can see both of them now.

348
00:13:18,626 --> 00:13:20,126
Dong-Reaper! In Na!

349
00:13:20,126 --> 00:13:21,326
I washed my face!

350
00:13:21,326 --> 00:13:22,959
Good job.

351
00:13:22,959 --> 00:13:24,596
You actually did it?

352
00:13:24,596 --> 00:13:26,193
I washed my face and put on sunscreen.

353
00:13:26,193 --> 00:13:28,633
- Really?
- I'm so proud of you!

354
00:13:29,493 --> 00:13:32,159
[Praised just for washing her face]
You're absolutely glowing.

355
00:13:32,159 --> 00:13:34,460
- Thank you!
- You're adorable.

356
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:36,541
This is seriously so funny.

357
00:13:36,541 --> 00:13:37,776
Are you putting on makeup?

358
00:13:37,776 --> 00:13:39,992
Just my eyebrows!

359
00:13:39,992 --> 00:13:42,754
- She barely wears any makeup anyway.
- Want me to do your eyebrows?

360
00:13:42,754 --> 00:13:44,049
Oh, honestly.

361
00:13:44,049 --> 00:13:46,726
She's just playing with makeup.

362
00:13:46,726 --> 00:13:47,786
She looks exactly the same!

363
00:13:47,786 --> 00:13:50,022
Makeup should give you a before and after,

364
00:13:50,022 --> 00:13:51,793
but she looks exactly the same.

365
00:13:51,793 --> 00:13:53,091
You're so annoying.

366
00:13:53,091 --> 00:13:54,193
- You know I'm right.
- No, you're not.

367
00:13:54,193 --> 00:13:56,762
- It only counts if you look different.
- I do look different. Look.

368
00:13:56,762 --> 00:13:58,764
- Can I touch your hair?
- Sure.

369
00:13:58,764 --> 00:14:00,165
- Is it wet, or did you put something in it?
- No.

370
00:14:00,165 --> 00:14:01,726
- I washed my face too.
- Really?

371
00:14:01,726 --> 00:14:03,602
It wasn't just Eun Tak.

372
00:14:03,602 --> 00:14:04,903
I washed my face,

373
00:14:04,903 --> 00:14:06,293
and I put on sunscreen too.

374
00:14:06,293 --> 00:14:07,439
Oh, good.

375
00:14:07,439 --> 00:14:09,026
But he looks so handsome now.

376
00:14:09,026 --> 00:14:12,493
Earlier, when I saw him washing up,

377
00:14:12,493 --> 00:14:15,180
he was making these awful gagging noises.

378
00:14:15,180 --> 00:14:17,226
- He was probably brushing his teeth.
- I was brushing my teeth.

379
00:14:17,226 --> 00:14:19,626
- That was probably it.
- When you brush your teeth...

380
00:14:19,626 --> 00:14:21,820
Everyone makes noises like that.

381
00:14:21,820 --> 00:14:24,359
[In Na finds her next target]

382
00:14:24,359 --> 00:14:26,658
And I thought, "Is that really Gong Yoo?"

383
00:14:26,658 --> 00:14:30,162
Why is the Goblin in my head acting like that?

384
00:14:30,162 --> 00:14:31,092
- What is he doing?
- Hey.

385
00:14:31,092 --> 00:14:33,092
Okay, enough.
I can't keep this image up anymore.

386
00:14:33,092 --> 00:14:35,359
Because it's too much for him,
he keeps trying to ruin the fantasy

387
00:14:35,359 --> 00:14:36,827
by acting even more ridiculous

388
00:14:36,827 --> 00:14:38,770
- and making those gagging noises.
- That's not it.

389
00:14:38,770 --> 00:14:41,073
- It won't work.
- That's who I really am.

390
00:14:41,073 --> 00:14:42,193
- I know.
- Exactly.

391
00:14:42,193 --> 00:14:43,626
- I'm saying it still won't work.
- I'm done trying.

392
00:14:43,626 --> 00:14:45,811
[A very human 949-year-old Goblin]

393
00:14:45,811 --> 00:14:47,312
- We're eating outside, right?
- I didn't see anything.

394
00:14:47,312 --> 00:14:48,193
- Let's do that.
- Yeah.

395
00:14:48,193 --> 00:14:50,148
I didn't see anything.

396
00:14:52,593 --> 00:14:53,918
Out here?

397
00:14:53,918 --> 00:14:55,526
- Really?
- Food always tastes better outside.

398
00:14:55,526 --> 00:14:57,356
That'll be so good.

399
00:14:57,356 --> 00:14:59,426
How many packs of ramen? Two?

400
00:14:59,426 --> 00:15:01,393
We have yukgaejang,
so should we make two packs?

401
00:15:01,393 --> 00:15:02,894
- Yeah.
- I'm hungry.

402
00:15:02,894 --> 00:15:04,962
We can add rice to the soup too.

403
00:15:05,831 --> 00:15:09,034
[The spicy yukgaejang stirs up appetites]
I woke up kind of hungry, actually.

404
00:15:09,034 --> 00:15:11,536
[In goes the green onion]

405
00:15:12,771 --> 00:15:16,660
[The broth gets better as it simmers]

406
00:15:16,660 --> 00:15:18,643
- Add a little more water.
- Okay.

407
00:15:18,643 --> 00:15:20,512
Otherwise, it'll keep boiling away.

408
00:15:20,512 --> 00:15:22,681
[Dong Wook makes the squid ramen]

409
00:15:22,681 --> 00:15:24,716
I like my noodles on the firm side.

410
00:15:24,716 --> 00:15:26,017
Then let's eat now.

411
00:15:26,017 --> 00:15:27,326
I think it's ready.

412
00:15:27,326 --> 00:15:28,653
This looks amazing.

413
00:15:28,653 --> 00:15:29,988
[Plump, tender bigfin squid]

414
00:15:29,988 --> 00:15:31,456
That looks so good.

415
00:15:31,456 --> 00:15:34,058
Let me give it a taste.

416
00:15:34,659 --> 00:15:37,195
[Blow]

417
00:15:37,927 --> 00:15:41,066
[In Na takes the first bite]

418
00:15:41,066 --> 00:15:42,092
It's really good.

419
00:15:42,092 --> 00:15:42,992
- Is it good?
- It's really good.

420
00:15:42,992 --> 00:15:44,159
- Isn't it a little bland?
- No.

421
00:15:44,159 --> 00:15:45,326
- It's not?
- It's really good.

422
00:15:45,326 --> 00:15:46,972
It's really good.

423
00:15:46,972 --> 00:15:48,840
- Is it good?
- It's not bland.

424
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:51,460
[Snip]

425
00:15:51,460 --> 00:15:53,545
[Go Eun cuts the squid into small bites]
But this...

426
00:15:53,545 --> 00:15:55,313
That's it.

427
00:15:55,313 --> 00:15:56,159
- Bigfin squid.
- Hurry and serve yourself.

428
00:15:56,159 --> 00:15:57,216
[One bite]
No, you go ahead.

429
00:15:57,216 --> 00:15:59,393
- I'll serve you some.
- No, I can wait until you serve yourself.

430
00:15:59,393 --> 00:16:01,726
- It's only two packs, so there isn't much.
- The squid is good.

431
00:16:01,726 --> 00:16:03,159
- It really is.
- Is it?

432
00:16:03,159 --> 00:16:04,922
The squid...

433
00:16:06,359 --> 00:16:07,893
[Mmm]

434
00:16:07,893 --> 00:16:09,895
Go Eun, try it now. It's perfect.

435
00:16:09,895 --> 00:16:12,626
[Bigfin squid with the perfect chew]

436
00:16:12,626 --> 00:16:15,567
[Mmm]

437
00:16:15,567 --> 00:16:18,402
[A satisfying breakfast]

438
00:16:18,402 --> 00:16:22,240
[Whoa]
But... How did you cook it so perfectly?

439
00:16:22,974 --> 00:16:25,793
[Now for the ramen feast]

440
00:16:25,793 --> 00:16:27,945
- This is so good.
- Yeah.

441
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:32,450
- Good thing we let it cook a while.
- Yeah.

442
00:16:33,959 --> 00:16:35,726
- Eat up, everyone.
- You eat first.

443
00:16:35,726 --> 00:16:36,822
It's really good.

444
00:16:36,822 --> 00:16:37,989
- Is it?
- I'm telling you, it's really good.

445
00:16:37,989 --> 00:16:39,357
[You should eat too]
Everyone, eat up.

446
00:16:39,357 --> 00:16:40,827
[Still sleepy, Go Eun runs on coffee]
This coffee is so good.

447
00:16:40,827 --> 00:16:42,160
I really needed this.

448
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:43,562
I can't believe this.

449
00:16:43,562 --> 00:16:45,832
You aren't eating?

450
00:16:45,832 --> 00:16:47,359
- What's gotten into you?
- She has lost it.

451
00:16:47,359 --> 00:16:48,600
This isn't like you!

452
00:16:48,600 --> 00:16:52,059
- I know. Even I feel weird about it.
- Seriously.

453
00:16:52,059 --> 00:16:54,239
You put on makeup first thing in the morning...

454
00:16:54,239 --> 00:16:56,708
I didn't even get to finish my makeup.

455
00:16:56,708 --> 00:16:58,193
- That's her with makeup on.
- And now you won't even touch

456
00:16:58,193 --> 00:17:00,378
[A concerned word from Gong Yoo]
the hangover ramen.

457
00:17:00,378 --> 00:17:02,515
- Think you could get a little something down?
- This ramen is good.

458
00:17:02,515 --> 00:17:03,583
Just coffee?

459
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:06,886
[It's so good. Why won't she eat?]

460
00:17:07,760 --> 00:17:11,013
[Dong Wook's appetite kicks in]

461
00:17:11,013 --> 00:17:13,457
It's spicy!

462
00:17:16,092 --> 00:17:19,551
- Does the yukgaejang have glass noodles too?
- Yeah, I added glass noodles.

463
00:17:19,551 --> 00:17:21,032
[Next up: the spicy yukgaejang]
That looks good too.

464
00:17:21,032 --> 00:17:23,301
Why are you pushing yourself
when you can't handle spicy food?

465
00:17:23,301 --> 00:17:25,036
Yeah, but I still had to taste it.

466
00:17:25,036 --> 00:17:26,905
And I was hungry.

467
00:17:26,905 --> 00:17:29,240
- It's seriously spicy, though.
- Yeah.

468
00:17:31,043 --> 00:17:32,277
That one's probably spicy too.

469
00:17:32,277 --> 00:17:34,079
It's supposed to be spicy.

470
00:17:34,079 --> 00:17:37,148
See? That's why I said to mix in some gomtang.

471
00:17:37,148 --> 00:17:39,383
[Round two for the Goblin couple?]

472
00:17:40,051 --> 00:17:42,053
[Hissing]
Why do you keep saying no?

473
00:17:42,053 --> 00:17:43,588
[Haa...]

474
00:17:43,588 --> 00:17:44,723
Am I eating too much?

475
00:17:44,723 --> 00:17:46,726
- I'm not, right?
- No, you're fine.

476
00:17:46,726 --> 00:17:48,860
Don't worry about later. Just eat.

477
00:17:48,860 --> 00:17:51,997
What if Go Eun gets hungry again
in an hour or two?

478
00:17:51,997 --> 00:17:54,893
- We'll worry about that later.
- Oh, absolutely. One hundred percent!

479
00:17:54,893 --> 00:17:57,502
I'll walk past a sign and think,
"That looks so good,"

480
00:17:57,502 --> 00:17:58,737
[They know how hungry Go Eun gets]

481
00:17:58,737 --> 00:18:00,205
- and completely lose it.
- Then don't go out.

482
00:18:00,205 --> 00:18:03,041
- I really do lose it.
- Then don't go out at all. Just stay home.

483
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:04,177
Should we play yut, then?

484
00:18:04,177 --> 00:18:06,145
Sure.

485
00:18:06,145 --> 00:18:07,660
Let's all play a round of yut.

486
00:18:07,660 --> 00:18:10,020
- Do we have a yut set?
- I brought one.

487
00:18:10,020 --> 00:18:11,116
We'll play yut, and...

488
00:18:11,116 --> 00:18:12,126
All four of us?

489
00:18:12,126 --> 00:18:14,660
The only thing is,
the rules vary from place to place.

490
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:18,390
You have to play by my rules.

491
00:18:18,390 --> 00:18:21,059
Be careful when you play yut with Goblin.

492
00:18:21,059 --> 00:18:21,828
- Why?
- Why?

493
00:18:21,828 --> 00:18:24,159
[He takes yut very seriously]
He's touchy about the rules.

494
00:18:24,159 --> 00:18:24,997
- Competitive?
- No.

495
00:18:24,997 --> 00:18:26,765
My rules make it more fun.

496
00:18:26,765 --> 00:18:28,259
- Okay.
- Sounds good.

497
00:18:28,259 --> 00:18:30,436
- Right, we said we'd play yut.
- Hey, let's play on the porch.

498
00:18:30,436 --> 00:18:32,337
- Sounds good.
- How about cleanup?

499
00:18:32,337 --> 00:18:33,660
- The losing team cleans up after breakfast.
- Yeah.

500
00:18:33,660 --> 00:18:35,807
- Thanks for breakfast.
- Good.

501
00:18:35,807 --> 00:18:38,311
[A bucket-list game for Goblin]
I've always wanted to play yut on the porch.

502
00:18:38,311 --> 00:18:39,512
- The winning team...
- First, let's play rock-paper-scissors.

503
00:18:39,512 --> 00:18:40,412
The winning team...

504
00:18:40,412 --> 00:18:42,059
Rock-paper-scissors.

505
00:18:42,059 --> 00:18:43,393
Rock-paper-scissors.

506
00:18:43,393 --> 00:18:44,316
- Winner.
- Loser.

507
00:18:44,316 --> 00:18:45,216
- Winner.
- Huh?

508
00:18:45,216 --> 00:18:46,226
[Winner] [Loser] [Winner] [Loser]

509
00:18:46,226 --> 00:18:47,519
- Huh?
- We ended up like this again.

510
00:18:47,519 --> 00:18:49,722
How did we get the same teams again?

511
00:18:49,722 --> 00:18:52,358
Can we switch it up just once?

512
00:18:52,358 --> 00:18:55,593
Seriously, ten years later...
we're still on these teams?

513
00:18:55,593 --> 00:18:56,761
- These are the teams again?
- Yeah.

514
00:18:56,761 --> 00:18:59,026
- Big brother and little sister.
- Right, Team Siblings versus...

515
00:18:59,026 --> 00:19:00,665
- Team Siblings versus... What are we?
- Right.

516
00:19:00,665 --> 00:19:02,701
- Unlisted Souls.
- Yeah, Team Unlisted Souls.

517
00:19:02,701 --> 00:19:03,902
That was so good.

518
00:19:03,902 --> 00:19:05,560
Leave everything here.

519
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:06,905
- Okay.
- Got it.

520
00:19:06,905 --> 00:19:08,940
- The losing team cleans up.
- Dish duty.

521
00:19:08,940 --> 00:19:11,359
[One game, with dish duty on the line]

522
00:19:11,359 --> 00:19:12,744
One game decides it.

523
00:19:12,744 --> 00:19:14,212
One game.

524
00:19:14,212 --> 00:19:16,730
[Rummaging]

525
00:19:22,854 --> 00:19:24,289
[Onto the porch]

526
00:19:24,289 --> 00:19:26,092
[Plop]

527
00:19:26,092 --> 00:19:27,393
[Goblin brought his own yut set]

528
00:19:27,393 --> 00:19:29,928
Shouldn't we put something down?

529
00:19:29,928 --> 00:19:31,059
Do we spread this all the way out,

530
00:19:31,059 --> 00:19:32,664
- or fold it in half?
- Let's spread it all out.

531
00:19:32,664 --> 00:19:35,533
- If we spread it all out, we can sit on it too.
- No.

532
00:19:35,533 --> 00:19:37,570
We need an out-of-bounds area.

533
00:19:37,570 --> 00:19:39,860
- Oh, for when they fall off. Right.
- Out of bounds means no count.

534
00:19:39,860 --> 00:19:42,040
- But...
- No. I said we're playing by my rules.

535
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,660
No. I said we're playing by my rules.

536
00:19:43,660 --> 00:19:45,877
We can spread this one out
and put another mat on top.

537
00:19:45,877 --> 00:19:47,979
[Already exhausted]
Oh, come on. Why make it so complicated?

538
00:19:47,979 --> 00:19:51,383
- Then...
- Just sit down. It's clean.

539
00:19:51,383 --> 00:19:53,318
[Dong Wook just lets Goblin have his way]
Yeah, it's clean here.

540
00:19:53,318 --> 00:19:55,886
[Hmm...]

541
00:19:57,293 --> 00:19:58,426
Is this good? About this much space?

542
00:19:58,426 --> 00:19:59,524
[Test throw]
Isn't that too big?

543
00:19:59,524 --> 00:20:01,525
The sticks barely bounce on this.

544
00:20:01,525 --> 00:20:03,493
- It's too cushioned.
- Then what do you want me to do?

545
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:05,726
[Oh, brother...]

546
00:20:05,726 --> 00:20:07,400
What are you doing?

547
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,668
See? I told you.
I told you he gets touchy about yut.

548
00:20:09,668 --> 00:20:11,660
Just spread it out.
I'll spread the whole thing out. Sorry.

549
00:20:11,660 --> 00:20:14,393
- Spread it all out. All of it.
- My bad.

550
00:20:14,393 --> 00:20:15,341
[Test throw number two]

551
00:20:15,341 --> 00:20:16,775
- Nice. Yeah.
- Satisfied?

552
00:20:16,775 --> 00:20:18,910
If we spread it all out,
there's no out-of-bounds.

553
00:20:18,910 --> 00:20:21,359
We can just mark an out-of-bounds line.

554
00:20:21,359 --> 00:20:23,148
Should we use this? One of these or two?

555
00:20:23,148 --> 00:20:24,482
[The out-of-bounds line is set]
One is too small.

556
00:20:24,482 --> 00:20:26,351
Okay. Let's do that.

557
00:20:26,351 --> 00:20:27,952
All right.

558
00:20:27,952 --> 00:20:29,688
[Dish duty is on the line]
Let me explain the rules.

559
00:20:29,688 --> 00:20:31,956
I'm only explaining this once, so listen.

560
00:20:31,956 --> 00:20:34,392
- This is the starting point.
- Okay.

561
00:20:35,828 --> 00:20:37,729
[Three pieces per team]
- We said three pieces, right? - Three.

562
00:20:37,729 --> 00:20:40,031
Here's the important part.

563
00:20:40,031 --> 00:20:41,466
Go all the way around,

564
00:20:41,466 --> 00:20:43,101
[Once a piece makes a full lap]

565
00:20:43,101 --> 00:20:44,269
[1 point]
and you score.

566
00:20:44,269 --> 00:20:45,560
Normally, when you finish,

567
00:20:45,560 --> 00:20:48,173
[Usually, overshooting still scores]
you still score even if you roll too high.

568
00:20:48,173 --> 00:20:49,092
- Normally.
- Right.

569
00:20:49,092 --> 00:20:50,809
But we're not doing that.

570
00:20:50,809 --> 00:20:53,411
[You must land exactly to score]
You have to hit it exactly.

571
00:20:53,411 --> 00:20:54,426
Right.

572
00:20:54,426 --> 00:20:56,514
So if you're trying to finish from here,

573
00:20:56,514 --> 00:20:58,450
you need Do or Gae.

574
00:20:58,450 --> 00:20:59,651
[Only Gae scores from here]

575
00:20:59,651 --> 00:21:01,319
Geol won't count.

576
00:21:01,319 --> 00:21:04,222
[Overshooting doesn't count]

577
00:21:04,222 --> 00:21:06,291
[Back to the original spot]

578
00:21:06,291 --> 00:21:07,927
- Okay, this is a bust.
- Got it.

579
00:21:07,927 --> 00:21:09,059
It's a bust, but...

580
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:11,262
- How far out counts?
- If it touches the mat...

581
00:21:11,262 --> 00:21:13,865
- Then it's not a bust.
- Okay.

582
00:21:13,865 --> 00:21:15,234
[Got it]

583
00:21:15,234 --> 00:21:16,626
- See? Hey!
- That's way too...

584
00:21:16,626 --> 00:21:18,026
- Hey, it's barely touching.
- Yeah.

585
00:21:18,026 --> 00:21:18,870
Not a bust.

586
00:21:18,870 --> 00:21:21,873
Why do you have to say,
"It's not a bust," like that?

587
00:21:21,873 --> 00:21:23,126
- That's not the boundary.
- See? This is what makes it fun.

588
00:21:23,126 --> 00:21:24,876
Just try playing by my rules.

589
00:21:24,876 --> 00:21:26,311
[Three pieces per team]
[Only an exact finish scores]

590
00:21:26,311 --> 00:21:29,126
[Off the mat is a bust]
[Touching the mat still counts]

591
00:21:29,126 --> 00:21:31,116
- Okay.
- Okay.

592
00:21:31,116 --> 00:21:32,817
Here we go.

593
00:21:35,126 --> 00:21:37,422
- Let's fight.
- This could start a real fight.

594
00:21:37,422 --> 00:21:38,256
But let's fight.

595
00:21:38,256 --> 00:21:40,326
I really want to fight.

596
00:21:40,326 --> 00:21:42,992
[Team Siblings vs. Team Unlisted Souls]
Let's fight.

597
00:21:42,992 --> 00:21:44,393
- Here we go.
- Yeah.

598
00:21:44,393 --> 00:21:46,126
[Morning dishes are on the line]
We'll go second. You go first.

599
00:21:46,126 --> 00:21:47,326
[One game of yut decides it]
You want to go second?

600
00:21:47,326 --> 00:21:49,300
- Eun Tak, you throw.
- Me? I'm going first?

601
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,168
[Team Unlisted Souls goes first]
Go.

602
00:21:52,460 --> 00:21:54,526
- Geol.
- Geol.

603
00:21:54,526 --> 00:21:56,593
Three spaces.

604
00:21:56,593 --> 00:21:58,642
- Like this?
- Yes.

605
00:21:59,626 --> 00:22:01,579
And then...

606
00:22:01,579 --> 00:22:04,593
[Team Siblings is up]

607
00:22:04,593 --> 00:22:07,185
- Geol.
- Got you.

608
00:22:07,185 --> 00:22:09,253
[One captured on the very first throw]

609
00:22:11,660 --> 00:22:13,758
Oh, come on...

610
00:22:13,758 --> 00:22:16,126
- Then we get another throw.
- Because we captured a piece.

611
00:22:16,126 --> 00:22:18,563
So theirs goes back to start.

612
00:22:18,563 --> 00:22:20,865
- Gae.
- Oh, nice.

613
00:22:21,726 --> 00:22:22,934
We're taking the shortcut.

614
00:22:22,934 --> 00:22:24,102
At the crossroads.

615
00:22:24,102 --> 00:22:27,059
[He's clearly done this before]

616
00:22:27,059 --> 00:22:29,440
It's all luck. Pure luck.

617
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:31,509
- Bust!
- Team Bust.

618
00:22:31,509 --> 00:22:33,326
- Bust!
- Team Bust.

619
00:22:33,326 --> 00:22:35,193
Change their name to Team Bust.

620
00:22:35,193 --> 00:22:36,726
[Still stuck at the start]
We're okay.

621
00:22:36,726 --> 00:22:38,416
- Was it this way?
- That's right.

622
00:22:38,416 --> 00:22:39,284
[Sunny's first throw]
That's it.

623
00:22:39,284 --> 00:22:41,119
It's still touching!

624
00:22:41,119 --> 00:22:42,153
- It's Yut!
- Yut.

625
00:22:42,153 --> 00:22:43,688
- Go again.
- What?

626
00:22:43,688 --> 00:22:45,593
[Yut on her very first throw?]
- What? - Go again.

627
00:22:45,593 --> 00:22:47,927
I'm good at games like this.

628
00:22:47,927 --> 00:22:48,895
[Sunny gets another throw]

629
00:22:48,895 --> 00:22:50,829
- Yut and Gae.
- Gae.

630
00:22:50,829 --> 00:22:53,898
We'll just make a run for it
so they can't catch us.

631
00:22:53,898 --> 00:22:55,259
[Yut plus Gae: six spaces]

632
00:22:55,259 --> 00:22:57,001
She's good.

633
00:22:58,237 --> 00:23:00,571
Geol.

634
00:23:01,660 --> 00:23:03,560
Do.

635
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:05,159
Geol.

636
00:23:05,159 --> 00:23:06,860
It's Do.

637
00:23:06,860 --> 00:23:08,214
That's Gae.

638
00:23:08,214 --> 00:23:09,447
- Whose turn is it?
- It's me.

639
00:23:09,447 --> 00:23:11,293
[Four more spaces for a point]

640
00:23:11,293 --> 00:23:13,418
[Sunny of Team Siblings]

641
00:23:13,418 --> 00:23:15,159
[Three spaces]
- Geol. - Geol.

642
00:23:15,159 --> 00:23:17,222
- Geol.
- We'll bring out a new piece.

643
00:23:17,222 --> 00:23:18,323
Okay.

644
00:23:18,323 --> 00:23:20,091
[Their second piece is in play]

645
00:23:20,091 --> 00:23:23,329
[Closing in again]

646
00:23:23,329 --> 00:23:25,259
Eun Tak, roll Geol and take them.

647
00:23:25,259 --> 00:23:28,066
[Planning to capture them with Geol]

648
00:23:28,066 --> 00:23:29,900
Get them with Geol.

649
00:23:32,126 --> 00:23:33,059
Oh, what's this?

650
00:23:33,059 --> 00:23:35,660
- Back-do.
- Back-do.

651
00:23:35,660 --> 00:23:37,226
So Back-do is bad for them.

652
00:23:37,226 --> 00:23:39,244
[Back one space]
It's bad right now.

653
00:23:39,244 --> 00:23:41,293
[Aw...]

654
00:23:41,293 --> 00:23:42,547
- Gae.
- It's Gae.

655
00:23:42,547 --> 00:23:44,649
We'll take the shortcut again.

656
00:23:44,649 --> 00:23:46,326
[The pressure keeps building]

657
00:23:46,326 --> 00:23:48,286
Oh, we're in trouble. Big trouble.

658
00:23:48,286 --> 00:23:49,687
[A huge early lead]

659
00:23:49,687 --> 00:23:51,655
Eun Tak, we're in trouble.

660
00:23:54,026 --> 00:23:56,259
Geol.

661
00:23:56,259 --> 00:23:57,092
Go!

662
00:23:57,092 --> 00:23:59,326
[Run]
Go!

663
00:23:59,326 --> 00:24:01,560
[Sunny's up again]

664
00:24:01,560 --> 00:24:02,833
Mo!

665
00:24:02,833 --> 00:24:04,693
- Mo!
- Mo!

666
00:24:04,693 --> 00:24:05,904
Mo!

667
00:24:05,904 --> 00:24:07,426
[The yut goddess has arrived]
- Mo! - Mo!

668
00:24:07,426 --> 00:24:08,359
Mo!

669
00:24:08,359 --> 00:24:10,041
- Mo? What are you?
- I got Mo!

670
00:24:10,041 --> 00:24:11,426
- Mo?
- I really got Mo!

671
00:24:11,426 --> 00:24:12,877
- What are you?
- Come on!

672
00:24:12,877 --> 00:24:14,112
- Mo? What are you?
- I got Mo!

673
00:24:14,112 --> 00:24:15,380
- Mo?
- I really got Mo!

674
00:24:15,380 --> 00:24:16,860
[Speechless]
- What are you? - Come on!

675
00:24:16,860 --> 00:24:18,549
- Seriously, what are you?
- Mo.

676
00:24:18,549 --> 00:24:19,626
[Even their overreactions match]

677
00:24:19,626 --> 00:24:21,493
- What are you?
- Come on!

678
00:24:21,493 --> 00:24:22,560
- Seriously, what are you?
- Mo.

679
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:24,927
[How is this even possible?]
I'm telling you, I got Mo!

680
00:24:24,927 --> 00:24:26,925
- What happens when you roll Mo?
- Hold on. First, you get another throw.

681
00:24:26,925 --> 00:24:28,927
- I'll throw again.
- First, that's Mo.

682
00:24:28,927 --> 00:24:30,295
[Sunny gets another throw]

683
00:24:30,295 --> 00:24:31,963
- Geol.
- Geol.

684
00:24:31,963 --> 00:24:34,532
- Oh, that was way too good...
- Geol.

685
00:24:34,532 --> 00:24:36,226
[Current board]

686
00:24:36,226 --> 00:24:39,293
We'll combine Mo and Geol to move here.

687
00:24:39,293 --> 00:24:41,005
- Let's go here.
- Yeah.

688
00:24:41,005 --> 00:24:42,640
[Mo stacks the pieces]

689
00:24:42,640 --> 00:24:44,809
[Geol sends them down the shortcut]

690
00:24:44,809 --> 00:24:46,878
[All three pieces are near the finish]

691
00:24:46,878 --> 00:24:48,748
Whoa.

692
00:24:48,748 --> 00:24:50,386
- Mo.
- I really did get Mo.

693
00:24:50,386 --> 00:24:52,885
[Goblin has strategy, Sunny has luck]
Seriously, what are you?

694
00:24:52,885 --> 00:24:56,086
[Team Siblings has it all]

695
00:24:58,493 --> 00:24:59,873
- Are you starting a new piece?
- Yeah.

696
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:01,993
[Their second piece moves one space]

697
00:25:01,993 --> 00:25:04,493
[Team Siblings is nearing the finish]

698
00:25:04,493 --> 00:25:05,359
- It's Do.
- Do.

699
00:25:05,359 --> 00:25:06,593
- Got you!
- What did you catch?

700
00:25:06,593 --> 00:25:08,333
Oh, we don't have any pieces left to bring out.

701
00:25:08,333 --> 00:25:10,359
[All three are already in play]

702
00:25:10,359 --> 00:25:12,827
Will you stop capturing us already?

703
00:25:12,827 --> 00:25:15,506
[Two pieces move]
We'll move these two.

704
00:25:15,506 --> 00:25:16,808
We have to try something.

705
00:25:16,808 --> 00:25:18,643
[Team Unlisted Souls is in trouble]
Please.

706
00:25:18,643 --> 00:25:19,777
Please help us.

707
00:25:19,777 --> 00:25:21,359
This is such a rush.

708
00:25:21,359 --> 00:25:22,793
This is such a rush.

709
00:25:22,793 --> 00:25:23,960
- Yut.
- Yut.

710
00:25:23,960 --> 00:25:25,384
Time-out! Hold on...

711
00:25:25,384 --> 00:25:26,693
- Yut.
- Yut.

712
00:25:26,693 --> 00:25:28,152
Time-out! Hold on...

713
00:25:28,152 --> 00:25:29,827
- You pulled the mat...
- No, I didn't.

714
00:25:29,827 --> 00:25:31,723
- You pulled it, and the sticks moved...
- That's not what happened.

715
00:25:31,723 --> 00:25:33,559
[Did he move the mat?]
Not at all.

716
00:25:33,559 --> 00:25:34,693
Please help us.

717
00:25:34,693 --> 00:25:35,927
This is such a rush.

718
00:25:35,927 --> 00:25:37,259
[The mat shifts when he dodges]

719
00:25:37,259 --> 00:25:39,059
- Yut!
- Yut!

720
00:25:39,059 --> 00:25:41,760
Honestly... I only dodged
because I thought the sticks would hit me.

721
00:25:41,760 --> 00:25:44,827
Right. But you know the rule.
If they hit you, it's a bust.

722
00:25:44,827 --> 00:25:46,572
- Did they hit you? It's a bust?
- Tell us now.

723
00:25:46,572 --> 00:25:48,773
- Yeah. The sticks can't hit anyone.
- If they do, it's a bust?

724
00:25:48,773 --> 00:25:50,508
- It's a bust.
- Keep your knees off the mat.

725
00:25:50,508 --> 00:25:52,643
Stay out of the throwing area.

726
00:25:53,827 --> 00:25:56,249
This is so childish.

727
00:25:56,249 --> 00:25:58,992
[Even his teammate agrees]

728
00:25:58,992 --> 00:26:02,560
[Grim Reaper gets another throw]
Give me a big one first.

729
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:04,026
Gae.

730
00:26:04,026 --> 00:26:05,959
Yut and Gae.

731
00:26:05,959 --> 00:26:07,393
[Four plus two spaces]

732
00:26:07,393 --> 00:26:09,159
All right.

733
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:17,193
[Team Unlisted Souls' first piece]

734
00:26:17,193 --> 00:26:19,426
All right.

735
00:26:19,426 --> 00:26:20,927
[Double kill]
Got them.

736
00:26:20,927 --> 00:26:22,193
Send them back,

737
00:26:22,193 --> 00:26:24,075
then move up with Gae.

738
00:26:24,075 --> 00:26:25,810
This is so annoying.

739
00:26:25,810 --> 00:26:26,959
[One Do away from a point]

740
00:26:26,959 --> 00:26:28,012
Seriously?

741
00:26:28,012 --> 00:26:29,793
[So mad]

742
00:26:29,793 --> 00:26:30,815
Nice one.

743
00:26:30,815 --> 00:26:33,793
[The tables turn in an instant]

744
00:26:33,793 --> 00:26:35,853
[A celebration to rub it in]

745
00:26:35,853 --> 00:26:37,927
[Seething]

746
00:26:37,927 --> 00:26:40,626
Seriously... I'm so annoyed.

747
00:26:40,626 --> 00:26:42,060
I'm seriously annoyed.

748
00:26:42,060 --> 00:26:43,593
[Dancing with joy]

749
00:26:43,593 --> 00:26:45,159
I'm annoyed.

750
00:26:45,159 --> 00:26:46,726
I'm genuinely annoyed.

751
00:26:46,726 --> 00:26:47,732
Eun Tak.

752
00:26:47,732 --> 00:26:49,760
[The taunting begins]

753
00:26:49,760 --> 00:26:52,669
- I'm so annoyed.
