1004
00:36:03,587 --> 00:36:06,159
Then why'd you try it?

1005
00:36:06,159 --> 00:36:07,291
Blow it out.

1006
00:36:07,291 --> 00:36:08,392
[What about ten years later?]

1007
00:36:08,392 --> 00:36:09,493
Make a wish.

1008
00:36:09,493 --> 00:36:10,527
Get her a gift card.

1009
00:36:10,527 --> 00:36:13,560
[Goblin appears right on cue]

1010
00:36:13,560 --> 00:36:14,598
No way.

1011
00:36:14,598 --> 00:36:16,660
[10 years, 20 years, nothing changes]
[He'll always answer Eun Tak's call]

1012
00:36:16,660 --> 00:36:18,268
He'll always come when Eun Tak calls.

1013
00:36:18,268 --> 00:36:20,239
Right.

1014
00:36:20,239 --> 00:36:22,092
This is so fun.

1015
00:36:22,092 --> 00:36:24,126
[Eun Tak's Goblin, forever]
- This is fun. - I love it.

1016
00:36:24,126 --> 00:36:25,478
Right.

1017
00:36:25,478 --> 00:36:26,660
[Ding-dong]

1018
00:36:26,660 --> 00:36:29,245
- Huh?
- What was that?

1019
00:36:30,147 --> 00:36:32,560
- Did the doorbell just ring?
- Yeah.

1020
00:36:32,560 --> 00:36:34,617
Did the doorbell really just ring?

1021
00:36:35,285 --> 00:36:36,286
[Wait, this is...]

1022
00:36:36,286 --> 00:36:38,927
Our doorbell's never rung before.

1023
00:36:38,927 --> 00:36:40,092
What? Seriously?

1024
00:36:40,092 --> 00:36:41,337
- You thought of that scene too, right?
- Yeah.

1025
00:36:41,337 --> 00:36:42,726
Me too.

1026
00:36:42,726 --> 00:36:44,962
[This feels strangely familiar]
Did the doorbell really just ring?

1027
00:36:44,962 --> 00:36:46,359
[Ding-dong]

1028
00:36:46,359 --> 00:36:47,500
You got a text.

1029
00:36:47,500 --> 00:36:49,893
No, that's the doorbell!

1030
00:36:49,893 --> 00:36:52,393
It hasn't rung in 60 years.

1031
00:36:52,393 --> 00:36:53,506
What?

1032
00:36:53,506 --> 00:36:55,193
[Ding-dong]

1033
00:36:56,092 --> 00:36:59,245
[When Eun Tak first came to Goblin House]
None of us ever rings the doorbell.

1034
00:36:59,245 --> 00:37:02,426
[The doorbell rings for the first time]
Why'd you make that sound so creepy?

1035
00:37:02,426 --> 00:37:04,448
[The same chime rings here, too]
What? Seriously?

1036
00:37:04,448 --> 00:37:06,650
- Was that when Deok Hwa showed up?
- Who was it again?

1037
00:37:06,650 --> 00:37:08,252
No, it was Eun Tak.

1038
00:37:08,252 --> 00:37:10,788
[Who else would it be?]

1039
00:37:10,788 --> 00:37:11,860
Do we have a visitor?

1040
00:37:11,860 --> 00:37:12,927
No.

1041
00:37:12,927 --> 00:37:14,925
[No one's there]

1042
00:37:14,925 --> 00:37:17,695
But the doorbell should be around here.

1043
00:37:17,695 --> 00:37:20,760
- The front gate's right here.
- Wait, that's a letter.

1044
00:37:20,760 --> 00:37:22,566
- Huh?
- What?

1045
00:37:22,566 --> 00:37:24,568
[A letter in the mailbox?]

1046
00:37:24,568 --> 00:37:27,019
It's your list of the dead!

1047
00:37:27,019 --> 00:37:28,038
Hey.

1048
00:37:28,038 --> 00:37:31,075
[The Grim Reaper's list of the dead?]

1049
00:37:31,075 --> 00:37:32,704
[Ji Yeon Hee]
[Unknown]

1050
00:37:33,626 --> 00:37:34,712
Seriously?

1051
00:37:34,712 --> 00:37:37,281
[A mysterious envelope at Goblin House]

1052
00:37:37,281 --> 00:37:39,183
Hey.

1053
00:37:39,183 --> 00:37:40,210
What is that?

1054
00:37:40,210 --> 00:37:42,986
[What's inside?]

1055
00:37:44,557 --> 00:37:47,191
No way.

1056
00:37:47,191 --> 00:37:48,926
Why are there so many?

1057
00:37:48,926 --> 00:37:50,326
I know what these are.

1058
00:37:50,326 --> 00:37:52,563
- These are the fan submissions.
- Seriously?

1059
00:37:52,563 --> 00:37:54,726
I'm getting goosebumps.

1060
00:37:54,726 --> 00:37:57,793
- They're the fan submissions.
- She really does have goosebumps!

1061
00:37:57,793 --> 00:37:59,059
No way.

1062
00:37:59,059 --> 00:38:01,271
- Are you a goose?
- Hold on.

1063
00:38:01,271 --> 00:38:04,073
[First a bird, now a goose?]
Let's pick them at random.

1064
00:38:05,159 --> 00:38:07,326
She's still covered in goosebumps.

1065
00:38:07,326 --> 00:38:08,512
I can't believe this.

1066
00:38:08,512 --> 00:38:10,359
[The surprise letters give In Na chills]

1067
00:38:10,359 --> 00:38:12,382
This is incredible.

1068
00:38:13,710 --> 00:38:15,619
[Guardian 10th Anniversary Stories &amp; Q&amp;A]

1069
00:38:15,619 --> 00:38:17,299
[Share your story
and bring Kim Shin, Ji Eun Tak,]

1070
00:38:17,299 --> 00:38:18,789
[the Grim Reaper, and Sunny back
after ten years]

1071
00:38:18,789 --> 00:38:20,190
[A decade of love from Guardian fans]

1072
00:38:20,190 --> 00:38:22,659
[Guardian: The ultimate winter binge-watch]
[Happy 10th Anniversary to Guardian!]

1073
00:38:22,659 --> 00:38:25,962
[A decade later, it still gives us butterflies]
[Even now, the finale still moves me to tears]

1074
00:38:27,259 --> 00:38:28,465
Go ahead and pick one.

1075
00:38:28,465 --> 00:38:32,669
[Their heartfelt stories have arrived]

1076
00:38:33,526 --> 00:38:35,860
[Fans who've been with Guardian for ten years]
This means so much.

1077
00:38:35,860 --> 00:38:37,207
Seriously.

1078
00:38:37,207 --> 00:38:39,111
[have sent in story after story]
This is incredible.

1079
00:38:39,111 --> 00:38:43,246
[They read each message with gratitude]

1080
00:38:44,059 --> 00:38:46,583
"Hello. I'm a high school student

1081
00:38:46,583 --> 00:38:48,752
who's watched Guardian over ten times."

1082
00:38:48,752 --> 00:38:49,653
[A high school student?]
Huh?

1083
00:38:49,653 --> 00:38:52,760
"I was eight when the show first aired,

1084
00:38:52,760 --> 00:38:56,226
and now I'm eighteen."

1085
00:38:56,226 --> 00:38:58,526
Eight years old...

1086
00:38:58,526 --> 00:39:01,765
She watched it every winter, once a year.

1087
00:39:01,765 --> 00:39:04,168
"Because of Guardian, visiting Quebec

1088
00:39:04,168 --> 00:39:05,793
has been on my bucket list,

1089
00:39:05,793 --> 00:39:08,226
so I started saving up!"

1090
00:39:08,226 --> 00:39:10,474
I'm not done talking...

1091
00:39:10,474 --> 00:39:12,309
"I want to visit the hill and the hotel,

1092
00:39:12,309 --> 00:39:14,011
the spot where Eun Tak caught the falling leaf,

1093
00:39:14,011 --> 00:39:16,380
and the café where she blew out a candle

1094
00:39:16,380 --> 00:39:19,883
after getting her memories back.

1095
00:39:19,883 --> 00:39:22,886
I started saving in eighth grade,

1096
00:39:22,886 --> 00:39:25,556
and I've already saved 2.2 million won."

1097
00:39:25,556 --> 00:39:27,393
[That's amazing!]

1098
00:39:27,393 --> 00:39:32,029
Eun Tak, cheer her on with her favorite line.

1099
00:39:32,029 --> 00:39:33,597
"It's midnight!

1100
00:39:33,597 --> 00:39:34,932
It's January 1st!

1101
00:39:34,932 --> 00:39:37,233
I just became an adult!"

1102
00:39:39,736 --> 00:39:41,505
[The moment she turned 20]
It's midnight!

1103
00:39:41,505 --> 00:39:42,706
It's January 1st!

1104
00:39:42,706 --> 00:39:45,141
[Eun Tak rushes to tell Goblin]
I just became an adult!

1105
00:39:46,026 --> 00:39:47,711
"I just became an adult!"

1106
00:39:47,711 --> 00:39:52,092
[Just as adorable as ten years ago]
[Yeah, yeah!]

1107
00:39:52,092 --> 00:39:53,827
- I haven't heard that in ages.
- Seriously.

1108
00:39:53,827 --> 00:39:55,159
[A little shy]
You've got this!

1109
00:39:55,159 --> 00:39:57,053
You've got this!

1110
00:39:58,088 --> 00:40:01,251
[A heartfelt cheer from Eun Tak]
It's nice seeing that again.

1111
00:40:02,585 --> 00:40:06,276
Alright, "Hello, I used to pride myself
on being a Guardian fan,

1112
00:40:06,276 --> 00:40:08,588
but I met someone
who's an even bigger fan than I am,

1113
00:40:08,588 --> 00:40:10,168
and now I'm preparing for our wedding
as the groom-to-be."

1114
00:40:10,168 --> 00:40:11,815
[The groom-to-be?]
- Wow! - Oh.

1115
00:40:11,815 --> 00:40:16,997
"My fiancée has chosen Guardian
as her all-time favorite drama.

1116
00:40:16,997 --> 00:40:20,842
So, we've watched Guardian together
about ten times already!"

1117
00:40:20,842 --> 00:40:22,441
He really went through a lot.

1118
00:40:22,441 --> 00:40:24,547
"And she's watched it by herself

1119
00:40:24,547 --> 00:40:26,224
- more than 30 times."
- Wow!

1120
00:40:26,224 --> 00:40:27,811
- Wow!
- How many hours would that be?

1121
00:40:27,811 --> 00:40:30,787
- Then she must have memorized all the lines.
- I know.

1122
00:40:30,787 --> 00:40:32,279
"Watching Guardian,

1123
00:40:32,279 --> 00:40:36,204
we've always dreamed of having
a heartwarming marriage like that."

1124
00:40:36,204 --> 00:40:38,530
[Confused]
"A heartwarming marriage like that."

1125
00:40:38,530 --> 00:40:41,455
- Why are you frowning? Why?
- "Heartwarming?"

1126
00:40:41,455 --> 00:40:42,508
[Flustered]
No.

1127
00:40:42,508 --> 00:40:47,734
"Especially, the Grim Reaper and Sunny's
fated love was so moving that

1128
00:40:47,734 --> 00:40:50,863
it made us wonder if
that's how life is meant to be."

1129
00:40:50,863 --> 00:40:52,971
Oh.

1130
00:40:52,971 --> 00:40:55,081
I missed you.

1131
00:40:58,482 --> 00:41:03,350
"Do you think Sunny and the Grim Reaper
stayed happy together in their next life?"

1132
00:41:03,350 --> 00:41:05,017
Oh...

1133
00:41:05,017 --> 00:41:08,719
"And if you happen to read this message,

1134
00:41:08,719 --> 00:41:11,463
we'd love for you to celebrate
our marriage with us."

1135
00:41:11,463 --> 00:41:12,875
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations on your wedding.

1136
00:41:12,875 --> 00:41:14,046
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations!

1137
00:41:14,046 --> 00:41:15,620
Wow, I'm really jealous.

1138
00:41:15,620 --> 00:41:16,969
- I know.
- Yeah.

1139
00:41:16,969 --> 00:41:19,716
We'll celebrate with you
from the bottom of our hearts...

1140
00:41:19,716 --> 00:41:23,939
<i>♪ Congratulations on your wedding ♪</i>

1141
00:41:23,939 --> 00:41:25,888
- Congratulations... yeah.
- Congratulations!

1142
00:41:25,888 --> 00:41:28,238
I'll read the next submission.

1143
00:41:28,238 --> 00:41:30,260
Oh? This one...

1144
00:41:30,260 --> 00:41:31,484
Goblin, you should listen
carefully to this one.

1145
00:41:31,484 --> 00:41:32,282
Okay.

1146
00:41:32,282 --> 00:41:34,597
"Hello, I'm a freshman
who started college this year,

1147
00:41:34,597 --> 00:41:36,751
and the eldest daughter among three siblings."

1148
00:41:36,751 --> 00:41:37,815
Wow!

1149
00:41:37,815 --> 00:41:41,227
"I thought of my mom, a longtime Gong Yoo fan.

1150
00:41:41,227 --> 00:41:41,825
[Mom?]

1151
00:41:41,825 --> 00:41:44,240
I couldn't just pass by
without sending this message."

1152
00:41:44,240 --> 00:41:45,278
You thought...

1153
00:41:45,278 --> 00:41:47,753
- she was going to say she liked you, huh?
- Why are you laughing?

1154
00:41:47,753 --> 00:41:51,244
- She suddenly said, "my mom," and he froze.
- Why are you laughing?

1155
00:41:52,996 --> 00:41:54,540
"Whenever Mr. Gong Yoo appears,

1156
00:41:54,540 --> 00:41:58,320
my mom runs to the TV shouting, 'Oppa!'
like a teenage girl!

1157
00:41:58,320 --> 00:42:00,578
My dad has now completely accepted it,

1158
00:42:00,578 --> 00:42:03,822
and seems to acknowledge
my mom's love for Mr. Gong Yoo."

1159
00:42:03,822 --> 00:42:06,080
"My dad has now completely accepted it..."

1160
00:42:06,080 --> 00:42:10,502
"My mom always says that
I should marry a man like Mr. Gong Yoo."

1161
00:42:10,502 --> 00:42:13,918
- "I like Mr. Lee Dong Wook too, though."
- "Too."

1162
00:42:13,918 --> 00:42:15,158
[Trying to stay calm]

1163
00:42:15,158 --> 00:42:16,426
"In your opinion, Mr. Gong Yoo,

1164
00:42:16,426 --> 00:42:20,740
do you think you're a good man?
I'm really curious."

1165
00:42:21,434 --> 00:42:24,529
- We know the answer to that.
- Right, you two tell us.

1166
00:42:24,529 --> 00:42:28,409
- He's truly a good person and a good man.
- That's right.

1167
00:42:28,409 --> 00:42:29,576
[Shy]

1168
00:42:29,576 --> 00:42:34,100
Back then, I just liked him
because he was like my older brother!

1169
00:42:34,100 --> 00:42:36,105
- He's handsome and cool.
- Yeah.

1170
00:42:36,105 --> 00:42:38,374
I mean, he's really cool!
So that's why I liked him.

1171
00:42:38,374 --> 00:42:41,972
But now, it's not because of that.
I like him because he's genuinely sincere.

1172
00:42:41,972 --> 00:42:44,235
- That's right.
- He's a truly mature person.

1173
00:42:44,235 --> 00:42:47,330
Though we don't know what he'd be like
if you met him as a romantic partner.

1174
00:42:48,210 --> 00:42:50,433
Oh! A good person and a good man
aren't necessarily the same thing.

1175
00:42:50,433 --> 00:42:52,527
- They're different.
- They're completely different.

1176
00:42:52,527 --> 00:42:55,720
With a face like his,
being this considerate is already impressive.

1177
00:42:55,720 --> 00:42:57,250
Did you see this?

1178
00:42:57,250 --> 00:42:59,155
"With a face like his,
being this considerate..."

1179
00:42:59,155 --> 00:43:03,240
W-With looks like this, this kind of height,
and this level of popularity,

1180
00:43:03,240 --> 00:43:05,144
that's already pretty good.

1181
00:43:05,144 --> 00:43:07,125
Alright, okay! Thank you! Thank you so much!

1182
00:43:07,125 --> 00:43:09,712
I'll try to live even better from now on.

1183
00:43:09,712 --> 00:43:11,973
- That's what really matters.
- I know.

1184
00:43:11,973 --> 00:43:14,058
Let's read the next story first!

1185
00:43:14,058 --> 00:43:17,264
Because I think she's got another rival here.

1186
00:43:17,264 --> 00:43:19,904
- Here it is. Let's read this one first.
- Let's go, let's go.

1187
00:43:19,904 --> 00:43:21,958
Please wait just a moment.

1188
00:43:22,583 --> 00:43:24,254
"From middle school through high school,

1189
00:43:24,254 --> 00:43:27,385
- I rewatched it more than 40 times."
- Wow!

1190
00:43:27,385 --> 00:43:29,825
- "I rewatched it more than 40 times."
- Wow!

1191
00:43:29,825 --> 00:43:31,855
- That's amazing.
- "Guardian was...

1192
00:43:31,855 --> 00:43:33,886
a part of my entire school life.

1193
00:43:33,886 --> 00:43:36,254
It's kind of funny, but back in middle school,

1194
00:43:36,254 --> 00:43:39,798
I thought a handsome older guy
who looked like Gong Yoo would show up

1195
00:43:39,798 --> 00:43:42,549
with a bouquet of buckwheat flowers
by my senior year.

1196
00:43:42,549 --> 00:43:44,718
But my actual senior year was just..."

1197
00:43:44,718 --> 00:43:48,793
"Before I knew it, I was a college freshman
in the major I'd always wanted,

1198
00:43:48,793 --> 00:43:51,052
but my favorite drama is still Guardian."

1199
00:43:51,052 --> 00:43:52,255
Now, this is the important part!

1200
00:43:52,255 --> 00:43:54,182
"To Gong Yoo...

1201
00:43:55,230 --> 00:43:59,018
Mister, I love you! I'm going to marry you!"

1202
00:43:59,965 --> 00:44:01,350
- What are you going to do, Gong Yoo?
- Oh...

1203
00:44:01,350 --> 00:44:02,547
- she's just informing you?
- Yeah.

1204
00:44:02,547 --> 00:44:03,601
- Informing...
- She's going to marry you.

1205
00:44:03,601 --> 00:44:06,835
- What are you going to do?
- Come marry me!

1206
00:44:06,835 --> 00:44:09,045
- Tell her to come.
- He's saying, "Come marry me."

1207
00:44:09,045 --> 00:44:10,456
- Come on.
- Yoon Seo.

1208
00:44:10,456 --> 00:44:13,382
- We're in Yangyang right now, but...
- Wait, wait.

1209
00:44:13,382 --> 00:44:15,882
- Isn't she young enough to be my daughter?
- That's right.

1210
00:44:15,882 --> 00:44:17,635
- How old is she?
- 20.

1211
00:44:18,348 --> 00:44:22,517
But you're 949 years old anyway, so...
does age even mean anything?

1212
00:44:22,517 --> 00:44:26,646
- She's young enough to be his daughter.
- Well, age is just a number,

1213
00:44:26,646 --> 00:44:29,765
but she has such a bright future ahead of her.

1214
00:44:29,765 --> 00:44:31,266
I'd feel a little guilty.

1215
00:44:31,266 --> 00:44:34,676
So I think this amount of distance
between us is just right.

1216
00:44:34,676 --> 00:44:36,057
She probably didn't really mean it.

1217
00:44:36,057 --> 00:44:37,665
[Flustered]

1218
00:44:37,665 --> 00:44:38,775
- She wasn't serious, was she?
- That's right.

1219
00:44:38,775 --> 00:44:40,241
- That's right.
- She was just saying it.

1220
00:44:40,241 --> 00:44:42,157
[TIME]
But, wait... time out for a second.

1221
00:44:42,157 --> 00:44:46,369
- The Goblin's bride is still alive, you know.
- Yeah, she is.

1222
00:44:46,369 --> 00:44:49,907
[The Goblin bride's remarks, 10 years later]
Oh, that would be a problem. Yeah...

1223
00:44:49,907 --> 00:44:52,770
- Because... I'm still alive, after all.
- She says no.

1224
00:44:52,770 --> 00:44:54,079
That's right, that's right.

1225
00:44:54,079 --> 00:44:56,945
[Filled with laughter, thanks to our fans]

1226
00:44:56,945 --> 00:44:58,980
So, what are we doing now?

1227
00:44:58,980 --> 00:45:01,377
Now? Riding bicycles?

1228
00:45:01,377 --> 00:45:06,343
- It's been a while. I'm exhausted.
- These bicycles are so cute.

1229
00:45:06,343 --> 00:45:07,783
Oh, you're right.

1230
00:45:07,783 --> 00:45:09,488
That's the kind of bike
you'd ride to the market.

1231
00:45:09,488 --> 00:45:13,189
[Next bucket list: Ride bicycles together]
It looks like it needs a baguette in the front.

1232
00:45:13,189 --> 00:45:15,860
Goblin, which color do you want? Blue or green?

1233
00:45:15,860 --> 00:45:20,981
- Me? Sky blue! I want sky blue!
- Yeah? Sky blue? Then I'll take the green one.

1234
00:45:20,981 --> 00:45:22,428
Oh, they're different colors.

1235
00:45:22,428 --> 00:45:25,760
- That's cute.
- What color do you want? Pink or purple?

1236
00:45:25,760 --> 00:45:28,311
- I'll take purple.
- Purple? Yeah.

1237
00:45:28,311 --> 00:45:32,168
Alright, bring it over here. Walk it over here.
It's too hard to ride it down.

1238
00:45:32,168 --> 00:45:35,501
[Looking serious,
putting on helmets for a safe ride]

1239
00:45:35,501 --> 00:45:37,837
Alright, come over here.

1240
00:45:40,602 --> 00:45:43,209
[An excited Goblin]
Hey, it actually has gears.

1241
00:45:44,882 --> 00:45:46,340
Do you think we'll even need to use the gears?

1242
00:45:46,340 --> 00:45:48,194
[The Goblin and the Grim Reaper
are first at the starting line]

1243
00:45:48,194 --> 00:45:50,477
- Are you all ready, Go Eun?
- Yep.

1244
00:45:50,477 --> 00:45:52,292
Let's go!

1245
00:45:52,292 --> 00:45:56,341
[Go Eun sets off excitedly too!]

1246
00:45:56,341 --> 00:45:58,180
Wow!

1247
00:45:58,180 --> 00:46:00,022
Hey, careful, careful!

1248
00:46:00,022 --> 00:46:02,600
Careful, careful! Be careful!

1249
00:46:02,600 --> 00:46:03,625
Be careful!

1250
00:46:03,625 --> 00:46:07,079
[The older brothers startled by the youngest]

1251
00:46:07,079 --> 00:46:08,087
Be careful!

1252
00:46:08,087 --> 00:46:10,272
[Eun Tak is simply thrilled
to be riding a bicycle]

1253
00:46:10,272 --> 00:46:15,169
- Wow, she's really fearless.
- Eun Tak, like that... um...

1254
00:46:15,169 --> 00:46:17,514
Put your phone in the basket.
It looks like it might fall out.

1255
00:46:17,514 --> 00:46:18,539
- My... oh.
- Yeah.

1256
00:46:18,539 --> 00:46:21,437
[The older brothers just can't
stop worrying about Eun Tak]

1257
00:46:21,437 --> 00:46:23,558
Is mine okay?
Something feels a little strange...

1258
00:46:23,558 --> 00:46:25,470
- What part?
- This is...

1259
00:46:25,470 --> 00:46:26,637
Want me to tighten this?

1260
00:46:26,637 --> 00:46:28,789
[So caring]
I think it's on wrong.

1261
00:46:29,609 --> 00:46:31,796
Is my hair okay?

1262
00:46:31,796 --> 00:46:32,835
- Me?
- Me.

1263
00:46:32,835 --> 00:46:34,976
- Gong Yoo, you look handsome.
- Not you, me.

1264
00:46:34,976 --> 00:46:36,254
Yours is fine.

1265
00:46:36,254 --> 00:46:37,652
- You look nice.
- Oh, okay.

1266
00:46:37,652 --> 00:46:39,055
- What do we do? Go?
- Yeah.

1267
00:46:39,055 --> 00:46:40,350
- Let's go!
- Do you know the way?

1268
00:46:40,350 --> 00:46:43,024
- Do we just keep riding all the way to Seoul?
- Oh, oh...

1269
00:46:43,024 --> 00:46:47,179
- Beep beep!
- Oh... hey, am I pedaling properly?

1270
00:46:47,179 --> 00:46:49,490
You're doing great.

1271
00:46:49,490 --> 00:46:51,119
- What? Why?
- The pedals... oh...

1272
00:46:51,119 --> 00:46:52,804
- The pedals...
- Oh!

1273
00:46:52,804 --> 00:46:55,604
[A delightful bike ride along the sea breeze]

1274
00:46:56,448 --> 00:46:58,239
- It has gears! Gears!
- Gears?

1275
00:46:58,239 --> 00:47:01,235
Just turn the one on the right. Click, click.

1276
00:47:02,415 --> 00:47:05,035
[Whoosh]
I'm going to pass you.

1277
00:47:05,035 --> 00:47:06,487
I even passed the drone.

1278
00:47:06,487 --> 00:47:09,805
[Go Eun, the cycling expert, takes the lead]

1279
00:47:11,587 --> 00:47:14,473
[This is so fun]

1280
00:47:14,473 --> 00:47:18,971
[The Goblin gives chase with all his might]

1281
00:47:20,926 --> 00:47:23,084
[The Goblin takes back first place]

1282
00:47:23,084 --> 00:47:26,138
I'm filming you with my camera right now!

1283
00:47:26,138 --> 00:47:27,660
Like this.

1284
00:47:27,660 --> 00:47:28,748
[Gong Yoo's CAM]

1285
00:47:28,748 --> 00:47:31,350
Wow, this is fun!

1286
00:47:31,350 --> 00:47:32,969
Hi!

1287
00:47:34,365 --> 00:47:39,114
[Hello]

1288
00:47:39,114 --> 00:47:40,608
Hi!

1289
00:47:40,608 --> 00:47:43,362
[Gong Yoo and Go Eun
enjoy the refreshing breeze]

1290
00:47:43,362 --> 00:47:46,902
Wow, this feels so good!

1291
00:47:46,902 --> 00:47:48,161
[Dong Wook follows In Na slowly from behind]
That's right.

1292
00:47:48,161 --> 00:47:49,945
- You need to pick up a little speed.
- Oh, the gear...

1293
00:47:49,945 --> 00:47:53,072
- Ah, after adjusting the gears...
- That's it, that's it.

1294
00:47:53,072 --> 00:47:54,512
[So excited]
Wow, what's that over there?

1295
00:47:54,512 --> 00:47:57,515
Dong Wook! This is so much fun!

1296
00:47:57,515 --> 00:47:59,382
[Only worried about In Na]
Watch where you're going!

1297
00:48:02,549 --> 00:48:05,122
[Showing off some skills]
Wow, you're riding standing up?

1298
00:48:07,057 --> 00:48:08,083
Let's go up there!

1299
00:48:08,083 --> 00:48:11,085
That was actually my destination!
I've wanted to go there.

1300
00:48:11,085 --> 00:48:12,751
- Oh, really?
- Right, Dong Wook?

1301
00:48:12,751 --> 00:48:14,705
[An observatory located at Dongsan Beach]
- That's right. - We've wanted to go there.

1302
00:48:14,705 --> 00:48:17,305
- Let's go.
- Parking it...

1303
00:48:17,305 --> 00:48:20,376
- Wow, I'm out of breath just from riding that.
- I'm overheating.

1304
00:48:20,376 --> 00:48:21,906
[Goblin's out of breath after just one lap
around the neighborhood]

1305
00:48:21,906 --> 00:48:23,066
- It's nice.
- Are you out of breath?

1306
00:48:23,066 --> 00:48:24,666
Yeah.

1307
00:48:25,438 --> 00:48:28,836
Trying to pass you...

1308
00:48:32,304 --> 00:48:34,445
[The Peach Couple follows
behind the Goblin couple]

1309
00:48:34,445 --> 00:48:36,079
Let's go together!

1310
00:48:36,079 --> 00:48:37,406
- Everyone!
- Yeah?

1311
00:48:37,406 --> 00:48:39,377
Let's go together.

1312
00:48:39,377 --> 00:48:40,693
- Why? What's so funny?
- What?

1313
00:48:40,693 --> 00:48:42,293
I don't know.

1314
00:48:43,293 --> 00:48:45,960
[The gentle sea breeze
makes for perfect weather]

1315
00:48:45,960 --> 00:48:48,520
Ah, it feels so nice
climbing these stairs outdoors.

1316
00:48:48,520 --> 00:48:52,138
[Savoring the moment to the fullest]

1317
00:48:52,138 --> 00:48:56,448
Alright, keep climbing the stairs!
The stairs...

1318
00:49:00,544 --> 00:49:03,052
What if we hadn't come here?

1319
00:49:07,865 --> 00:49:09,028
This is so beautiful.

1320
00:49:09,028 --> 00:49:10,913
Wow! This is really amazing.

1321
00:49:10,913 --> 00:49:13,859
[A view that naturally leaves you in awe]

1322
00:49:19,144 --> 00:49:21,252
Wow, this is incredible.

1323
00:49:21,252 --> 00:49:23,570
I didn't know a place like this existed.

1324
00:49:23,570 --> 00:49:24,882
Wow, this is really beautiful.

1325
00:49:24,882 --> 00:49:28,675
[A hidden spot with stunning East Sea views]
It looks beautiful behind us, beside us,

1326
00:49:28,675 --> 00:49:30,308
and it's beautiful in front of us too.

1327
00:49:30,308 --> 00:49:32,429
Wow!

1328
00:49:32,429 --> 00:49:35,426
- The view's so different up here.
- Yeah.

1329
00:49:35,426 --> 00:49:36,643
- Wow...
- This is so beautiful!

1330
00:49:36,643 --> 00:49:38,563
I love it. I really love it.

1331
00:49:39,667 --> 00:49:42,061
Wow, the ocean is so clean.

1332
00:49:42,061 --> 00:49:44,517
The East Sea is really clean.

1333
00:49:44,517 --> 00:49:47,691
- You know "Beautiful?" Our song.
- I know.

1334
00:49:47,691 --> 00:49:50,154
I don't have my phone with me,
so play the song for us.

1335
00:49:50,154 --> 00:49:52,905
- Okay. I'll play it now?
- Make it dramatic.

1336
00:49:52,905 --> 00:49:57,878
[In Na's song request: "Beautiful" by Crush]

1337
00:50:00,124 --> 00:50:02,403
Now, it's complete! Complete.

1338
00:50:02,403 --> 00:50:04,522
- This is what you wanted to do?
- Yeah.

1339
00:50:04,522 --> 00:50:06,831
I think this song is what completes the moment.

1340
00:50:16,968 --> 00:50:25,433
[Still by each other's side after ten years]

1341
00:50:26,481 --> 00:50:30,038
Wow... this really is wonderful.

1342
00:50:30,038 --> 00:50:36,005
[A moment the four of them
will remember for a long time]

1343
00:50:37,026 --> 00:50:39,310
- This place really is amazing.
- It's really nice.

1344
00:50:39,310 --> 00:50:42,249
[Just being together is enough]

1345
00:50:49,407 --> 00:50:52,171
This is such a happy Saturday.

1346
00:50:52,930 --> 00:50:55,275
I guess people surf here too.

1347
00:50:56,589 --> 00:50:58,156
Jeez!

1348
00:50:58,156 --> 00:50:59,354
Seriously!

1349
00:50:59,354 --> 00:51:01,224
[Happy]

1350
00:51:02,055 --> 00:51:05,788
- I'm suddenly hungry.
- Yeah, I am getting hungry.

1351
00:51:06,745 --> 00:51:09,181
- This is...
- Here it is, Namgyeong Makguksu.

1352
00:51:09,181 --> 00:51:10,714
I'm going to eat a lot.

1353
00:51:10,714 --> 00:51:13,203
- Yeah, this place is supposed to be good.
- Really?

1354
00:51:13,936 --> 00:51:16,147
- Oh? Naengmyeon and makguksu!
- Where? Where?

1355
00:51:16,147 --> 00:51:18,379
- Right there.
- Over there.

1356
00:51:18,379 --> 00:51:20,448
Where do they sell stuffed squid?

1357
00:51:20,448 --> 00:51:22,591
Why? Do you want stuffed squid?

1358
00:51:22,591 --> 00:51:23,672
Yeah! I really want some!

1359
00:51:23,672 --> 00:51:25,566
There's a famous place that's known for...

1360
00:51:25,566 --> 00:51:28,249
- really good stuffed squid.
- Yeah, there was a really famous place.

1361
00:51:28,249 --> 00:51:30,119
I'm going there for the stuffed squid.

1362
00:51:30,119 --> 00:51:32,396
Really? You've already decided?

1363
00:51:32,396 --> 00:51:35,776
[Bucket list: Makguksu &amp; stuffed squid]
- Hello. - Hello.

1364
00:51:36,952 --> 00:51:41,956
But when you come to a place like this,
you've got to order the signature dishes first.

1365
00:51:41,956 --> 00:51:43,308
- Exactly!
- Yeah.

1366
00:51:43,308 --> 00:51:44,493
The basics...

1367
00:51:44,493 --> 00:51:46,224
How about two perilla-seed makguksu
and two gondre makguksu?

1368
00:51:46,224 --> 00:51:48,154
- Sounds good.
- And then stuffed squid.

1369
00:51:48,154 --> 00:51:49,675
- Good, good.
- Yeah.

1370
00:51:49,675 --> 00:51:51,090
- Two and two, plus one stuffed squid.
- No boiled pork, right?

1371
00:51:51,090 --> 00:51:52,771
- That's right.
- Thank you.

1372
00:51:52,771 --> 00:51:54,274
[Order: 2 Perilla-Seed Makguksu
2 Gondre Makguksu 1 Stuffed Squid]

1373
00:51:54,274 --> 00:51:56,203
I'm hungry first of all...

1374
00:51:57,840 --> 00:52:00,075
- Seriously...
- Why are you hungry again?

1375
00:52:00,075 --> 00:52:01,894
- Aren't you hungry?
- Yeah.

1376
00:52:01,894 --> 00:52:06,809
- But we ate a lot earlier.
- Yeah... but I'm still hungry.

1377
00:52:06,809 --> 00:52:08,550
- I'm always hungry.
- Still hungry after all that?

1378
00:52:08,550 --> 00:52:09,565
Exactly.

1379
00:52:09,565 --> 00:52:11,302
[Just then, the makguksu
and stuffed squid arrive]

1380
00:52:11,302 --> 00:52:12,329
- Wow!
- Wow!

1381
00:52:12,329 --> 00:52:14,469
Oh, this one doesn't have any broth.

1382
00:52:14,469 --> 00:52:16,406
- A brothy makguksu.
- Right.

1383
00:52:16,406 --> 00:52:24,466
[Mouthwatering makguksu and stuffed squid]

1384
00:52:24,466 --> 00:52:27,749
- Wow... this looks so delicious. Thank you.
- Go ahead and try it.

1385
00:52:27,749 --> 00:52:31,386
[Preparing to enjoy the meal with full respect]
Thank you for the meal.

1386
00:52:31,386 --> 00:52:34,333
[Perilla-Seed Makguksu]

1387
00:52:36,539 --> 00:52:37,633
[Gondre Makguksu]

1388
00:52:37,633 --> 00:52:42,451
- It's kind of like flavored with perilla oil.
- I think we should try this one first.

1389
00:52:42,451 --> 00:52:43,876
[They decide to try the gondre makguksu first]

1390
00:52:43,876 --> 00:52:46,384
Because the perilla flavor is stronger!

1391
00:52:46,384 --> 00:52:48,466
[Fragrant]

1392
00:52:59,802 --> 00:53:03,120
[It's so delicious!]

1393
00:53:06,431 --> 00:53:10,277
[The makguksu is just
as delicious as they hoped]

1394
00:53:10,277 --> 00:53:12,680
- Honestly...
- Now I see why it's so famous.

1395
00:53:12,680 --> 00:53:16,663
This is the best makguksu I've ever eaten!

1396
00:53:16,663 --> 00:53:19,008
[Agreed]
It's delicious.

1397
00:53:19,008 --> 00:53:20,705
Try this one too.

1398
00:53:21,344 --> 00:53:26,510
[After the gondre makguksu,
how will the perilla-seed makguksu taste?]

1399
00:53:31,931 --> 00:53:33,125
[This is the best]

1400
00:53:33,125 --> 00:53:34,920
It came up as the top spot, so...

1401
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:36,323
- Yum!
- That's right.

1402
00:53:36,323 --> 00:53:37,563
That's right.

1403
00:53:37,563 --> 00:53:39,139
The perilla flavor is so good.

1404
00:53:39,139 --> 00:53:42,009
[Rich and full of the nutty aroma
of perilla seeds]

1405
00:53:43,182 --> 00:53:49,182
[At this perfect moment,
they also try the stuffed squid]

1406
00:53:52,490 --> 00:53:54,842
Let's order three more of these!

1407
00:53:54,842 --> 00:53:56,911
What did you say?

1408
00:53:56,911 --> 00:53:59,061
Let's order three more of these.

1409
00:54:01,406 --> 00:54:03,815
Yoo In Na, stop pretending to be so brave.

1410
00:54:03,815 --> 00:54:06,559
She's all swagger in front of food.

1411
00:54:06,559 --> 00:54:09,815
[Checking if it's really
worth ordering three more]

1412
00:54:09,815 --> 00:54:11,350
Isn't it crazy?

1413
00:54:11,350 --> 00:54:12,433
[Just eat it already]

1414
00:54:12,433 --> 00:54:13,533
[Yep]

1415
00:54:13,533 --> 00:54:15,873
Wow, this is...

1416
00:54:15,873 --> 00:54:17,251
[A round of applause]
This is really delicious.

1417
00:54:17,251 --> 00:54:19,474
- The stuffed squid is delicious too.
- Yeah.

1418
00:54:19,474 --> 00:54:21,513
Can we order just one more stuffed squid?

1419
00:54:21,513 --> 00:54:23,654
- Are you serious?
- Sure!

1420
00:54:23,654 --> 00:54:26,417
Then everyone can have one more piece.

1421
00:54:28,326 --> 00:54:29,541
How do you do this...

1422
00:54:29,541 --> 00:54:31,921
[Um... excuse me...]
Ding-dong.

1423
00:54:31,921 --> 00:54:34,051
- What a dummy.
- Ding-dong.

1424
00:54:34,051 --> 00:54:36,874
[He keeps pressing the QR code instead]

1425
00:54:36,874 --> 00:54:40,475
[Orders are placed through the QR code]
- Here, the QR code. - Oh, seriously...

1426
00:54:40,475 --> 00:54:41,983
We'd like one more stuffed squid, please.

1427
00:54:41,983 --> 00:54:44,536
[Quick old-school ordering]
See? This is faster!

1428
00:54:44,536 --> 00:54:46,789
[Even in the drama, the Grim Reaper
wasn't good with technology]

1429
00:54:46,789 --> 00:54:49,299
[He doesn't even know how to make a video call]
You said you wanted to video call.

1430
00:54:49,299 --> 00:54:53,108
- I can't see your face.
- Hold your arm farther away.

1431
00:54:53,108 --> 00:54:54,741
Like this?

1432
00:54:55,717 --> 00:54:58,368
Oh, you scan this... to order...

1433
00:54:58,368 --> 00:55:01,358
Did you see how quickly
he said it to save his pride?

1434
00:55:01,358 --> 00:55:03,274
- "One more stuffed squid, please!"
- Yeah.

1435
00:55:03,274 --> 00:55:05,332
[In an incredible hurry]
We'd like one more stuffed squid, please.

1436
00:55:05,332 --> 00:55:08,574
I wanted to prove I wasn't wrong.

1437
00:55:09,307 --> 00:55:11,831
My choice wasn't wrong.

1438
00:55:12,707 --> 00:55:14,165
[Glancing over]

1439
00:55:14,165 --> 00:55:16,331
Um... if nobody else wants it...

1440
00:55:16,331 --> 00:55:18,754
- can I have the last piece of stuffed squid?
- Yeah!

1441
00:55:18,754 --> 00:55:21,251
If nobody else wants it,
can I have the last piece of stuffed squid?

1442
00:55:21,251 --> 00:55:23,006
[Only one piece of stuffed squid is left]
Yeah.

1443
00:55:23,006 --> 00:55:25,880
- Another one is coming anyway.
- Thanks, Dong Wook.

1444
00:55:25,880 --> 00:55:26,911
Were you staring at it

1445
00:55:26,911 --> 00:55:28,921
- and thinking about it the whole time?
- Yeah.

1446
00:55:28,921 --> 00:55:31,864
Right, the last piece
always makes you hesitate.

1447
00:55:31,864 --> 00:55:33,994
Come on! Why would you feel that way with us?

1448
00:55:33,994 --> 00:55:36,245
- Isn't that kind of a Korean thing?
- That's true.

1449
00:55:36,245 --> 00:55:37,808
[Typical Korean behavior,
everyone offers the last piece to someone else]

1450
00:55:37,808 --> 00:55:40,276
I think it's because
we have a culture of sharing, right?

1451
00:55:40,276 --> 00:55:42,825
- In other countries, everyone...
- Everyone usually has their own dish.

1452
00:55:42,825 --> 00:55:44,842
[Elsewhere, it's one dish per person]
"Mine is mine."

1453
00:55:44,842 --> 00:55:48,391
But even overseas... things have changed a lot.

1454
00:55:48,391 --> 00:55:50,702
- They share food too?
- Yeah, they do.

1455
00:55:50,702 --> 00:55:52,758
These days, people overseas enjoy Korean food,

1456
00:55:52,758 --> 00:55:55,407
[K-food &amp; culture go global]
so they're adopting Korean dining culture too.

1457
00:55:55,407 --> 00:55:57,888
K-culture is huge now.

1458
00:55:57,888 --> 00:56:00,561
If Guardian were released now,
it probably would've been different.

1459
00:56:00,561 --> 00:56:03,211
- If it aired now? The broadcast?
- I think so too!

1460
00:56:03,211 --> 00:56:05,551
Back then, there weren't
any streaming platforms.

1461
00:56:05,551 --> 00:56:06,663
That's true.

1462
00:56:06,663 --> 00:56:08,372
[Even more people might have watched it]
In that earlier message,

1463
00:56:08,372 --> 00:56:12,240
they said it's a drama that
still makes people watch reruns.

1464
00:56:12,240 --> 00:56:13,597
- That really resonated with me.
- Right.

1465
00:56:13,597 --> 00:56:15,156
I honestly love that.

1466
00:56:15,156 --> 00:56:17,667
I love having something like this
in my filmography.

1467
00:56:17,667 --> 00:56:20,147
- Yeah.
- It's an asset. A real asset.

1468
00:56:20,147 --> 00:56:22,693
- Congratulations, all three of you.
- Congratulations to you too.

1469
00:56:22,693 --> 00:56:24,161
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

1470
00:56:24,161 --> 00:56:27,840
Thanks for celebrating
Go Eun's 14th debut anniversary today.

1471
00:56:27,840 --> 00:56:31,609
<i>- ♪ Congratulations on your debut anniversary ♪</i>
- Let's skip that.

1472
00:56:31,609 --> 00:56:33,075
[Blowing]

1473
00:56:33,075 --> 00:56:36,074
[Goblin, what are you doing? Come over here!]

1474
00:56:36,074 --> 00:56:39,110
Oh, seriously...

1475
00:56:39,110 --> 00:56:41,668
[Even after ten years, he still gets called
over at every opportunity]

1476
00:56:41,668 --> 00:56:43,308
- Applause.
- Congratulations.

1477
00:56:43,308 --> 00:56:44,338
Applause.

1478
00:56:44,338 --> 00:56:46,985
[Mission accomplished, back to his seat]
Oh, seriously...

1479
00:56:46,985 --> 00:56:49,434
[A reward for getting summoned]

1480
00:56:49,434 --> 00:56:50,669
[Pushed him into it, then acting sweet]

1481
00:56:50,669 --> 00:56:54,015
Seriously... why do you always listen so well?

1482
00:56:55,263 --> 00:56:58,800
[Once a Goblin, always a Goblin]

1483
00:56:58,800 --> 00:57:01,941
- You didn't know each other before Guardian?
- Huh?

1484
00:57:01,941 --> 00:57:05,534
- The military!
- Did you attend together?

1485
00:57:05,534 --> 00:57:07,332
You don't "attend" the military.

1486
00:57:07,332 --> 00:57:08,906
[Oh... that's right...]
Oh...

1487
00:57:08,906 --> 00:57:10,801
You go in and come back out.

1488
00:57:10,801 --> 00:57:14,731
- Who says they "attend" the military?
- "Mom, I'm off to "attend" the military!"

1489
00:57:15,652 --> 00:57:17,217
What...

1490
00:57:17,217 --> 00:57:18,499
What is it, a university?

1491
00:57:18,499 --> 00:57:21,408
- Gotcha! You finally got her.
- After I went there and came back...

1492
00:57:21,408 --> 00:57:24,386
Ugh, why won't these military boots come off?

1493
00:57:24,386 --> 00:57:26,068
[One comment from In Na
gave everyone a reason to tease her]

1494
00:57:26,068 --> 00:57:29,679
You got one! Here we go again...
Ugh, I'm so tired of this.

1495
00:57:29,679 --> 00:57:33,013
"Mom! I need to bring 370,000 won
by next week to buy a gun."

1496
00:57:33,013 --> 00:57:35,723
It's not like you're paying
four years of college tuition.

1497
00:57:35,723 --> 00:57:37,349
[The price of saying one thing wrong]

1498
00:57:37,349 --> 00:57:39,136
So what are you actually trying to say?

1499
00:57:39,136 --> 00:57:43,044
- Did you meet in the military?
- Yeah.

1500
00:57:43,044 --> 00:57:45,252
But you really became close
while filming "Guardian," right?

1501
00:57:45,252 --> 00:57:46,551
That's right. We became much closer.

1502
00:57:46,551 --> 00:57:48,920
Working on the same project
and going through hardships together did that.

1503
00:57:48,920 --> 00:57:51,752
And back then in the military, I was a private.

1504
00:57:51,752 --> 00:57:53,318
I was the newest recruit,

1505
00:57:53,318 --> 00:57:54,511
- and he was a sergeant.
- You were?

1506
00:57:54,511 --> 00:57:56,102
- I was the most junior,
- Oh, you were a private?

1507
00:57:56,102 --> 00:57:58,129
and he was the most senior.

1508
00:57:58,129 --> 00:58:01,238
Just... he couldn't even look at me.

1509
00:58:01,238 --> 00:58:03,380
[Getting annoyed]
He couldn't even step on my shadow.

1510
00:58:03,380 --> 00:58:05,852
- Were you acting all high and mighty?
- I'll admit it now...

1511
00:58:05,852 --> 00:58:09,258
I washed all of Gong Yoo's underwear and socks.

1512
00:58:10,354 --> 00:58:11,882
- The Goblin's underwear?
- Yeah.

1513
00:58:11,882 --> 00:58:15,501
<i>♪ Goblin's underwear is nice and strong ♪</i>

1514
00:58:15,501 --> 00:58:18,851
[The Grim Reaper even did the Goblin's laundry]
<i>♪ Goblin's underwear is nice and strong ♪</i>

1515
00:58:18,851 --> 00:58:23,655
<i>- ♪ Tough and sturdy, too ♪</i>
- Stop it.

1516
00:58:23,655 --> 00:58:26,346
- Oh, this was your song?
- No, it wasn't.

1517
00:58:26,346 --> 00:58:29,586
What on earth did you do with your underwear
for it to become a song?

1518
00:58:29,586 --> 00:58:31,186
Was it...

1519
00:58:32,135 --> 00:58:34,039
especially manly?

1520
00:58:34,699 --> 00:58:36,666
I said stop it!

1521
00:58:40,178 --> 00:58:41,943
It has to be folded into perfectly
sharp edges, you know.

1522
00:58:41,943 --> 00:58:43,775
He is really good at it.

1523
00:58:43,775 --> 00:58:47,350
[Joking]
Basically... I raised Gong Yoo.

1524
00:58:48,075 --> 00:58:49,760
- It was only for a short time...
- Yeah, since it was ten years ago.

1525
00:58:49,760 --> 00:58:51,394
[The Goblin &amp; Grim Reaper, 20 Years Together]
what, two months? Three?

1526
00:58:51,394 --> 00:58:53,514
Yeah, maybe three or four months.

1527
00:58:53,514 --> 00:58:56,275
So if the four of us... would you
not want to do another drama together?

1528
00:58:56,275 --> 00:58:57,806
- Why wouldn't we?
- Of course we'd love to.

1529
00:58:57,806 --> 00:58:59,383
- There's no reason not to.
- What kind of drama?

1530
00:58:59,383 --> 00:59:01,199
What kind of drama would you want to do?

1531
00:59:01,199 --> 00:59:03,331
- Well, if we did one...
- Yeah.

1532
00:59:03,331 --> 00:59:05,959
- I actually thought about that earlier.
- You did?

1533
00:59:05,959 --> 00:59:07,788
[Lovers]
You know, honey... boyfriend...

1534
00:59:07,788 --> 00:59:09,840
And you two are married.

1535
00:59:09,840 --> 00:59:11,840
[Married couple?]
And I'm married too.

1536
00:59:11,840 --> 00:59:14,785
- But then...
- Ugh, this is exhausting already.

1537
00:59:14,785 --> 00:59:17,588
This turns into a romantic entanglement.

1538
00:59:17,588 --> 00:59:19,543
This is a complete love triangle mess.

1539
00:59:19,543 --> 00:59:21,425
I want us to fight constantly.

1540
00:59:21,425 --> 00:59:22,609
- Fight?
- Action?

1541
00:59:22,609 --> 00:59:24,394
- Action?
- No, with words.

1542
00:59:24,394 --> 00:59:26,047
[Fighting with words, not fists]
You know...

1543
00:59:26,047 --> 00:59:29,003
For example, we'd be a long-term couple

1544
00:59:29,003 --> 00:59:32,052
- and have really realistic fights.
- Totally realistic?

1545
00:59:32,052 --> 00:59:34,812
[A realistic conflict drama]
- Like, really real... - For real.

1546
00:59:34,812 --> 00:59:37,125
How could we possibly fight more?

1547
00:59:37,878 --> 00:59:39,566
Just imagine if there were no cameras.

1548
00:59:39,566 --> 00:59:40,951
That's exactly what I want to capture.

1549
00:59:40,951 --> 00:59:42,105
- Oh, you want to film that?
- Yeah.

1550
00:59:42,105 --> 00:59:44,910
- Us really fighting?
- A realistic portrayal of

1551
00:59:44,910 --> 00:59:46,440
how good we are at fighting...

1552
00:59:46,440 --> 00:59:48,076
I'll just do a melodrama about an affair.

1553
00:59:48,076 --> 00:59:50,734
But I don't want to do that kind of drama

1554
00:59:50,734 --> 00:59:53,116
- because then I'd have to manage my diet.
- Why?

1555
00:59:53,116 --> 00:59:54,427
Because I'd have to take my clothes off.

1556
00:59:54,427 --> 00:59:56,596
Oh my gosh, what's wrong with her? Our girl...

1557
00:59:56,596 --> 00:59:58,142
[Flustered... scandalized... dizzy...]
What's gotten into her?

1558
00:59:58,142 --> 01:00:00,781
- Honey, what's gotten into our girl?
- Do you absolutely need a bed scene?

1559
01:00:00,781 --> 01:00:02,125
[If you're doing a melodrama, do it properly!]
Yeah, of course.

1560
01:00:02,125 --> 01:00:03,575
Are you saying...

1561
01:00:03,575 --> 01:00:06,500
- an affair drama needs a bed scene by default?
- Then you won't take your clothes off?

1562
01:00:06,500 --> 01:00:09,355
- Yeah...
- Then do you just kiss in a melodrama?

1563
01:00:09,355 --> 01:00:11,299
Anyway...

1564
01:00:11,299 --> 01:00:13,791
Anyone, feel free to contact us.

1565
01:00:13,791 --> 01:00:15,385
If anyone wants to produce it.

1566
01:00:15,385 --> 01:00:19,532
[Quickly wrapping things up
before the melodrama gets out of hand]

1567
01:00:19,532 --> 01:00:21,112
Thanks for the meal.

1568
01:00:21,112 --> 01:00:23,939
- That was absolutely delicious.
- Yeah, thank you.

1569
01:00:25,660 --> 01:00:33,985
[With the soothing sound of the waves,
they can't help humming]

1570
01:00:33,985 --> 01:00:35,890
Oh my? He's moving.

1571
01:00:35,890 --> 01:00:37,415
[Director Gong is filming]
It's a video?

1572
01:00:37,415 --> 01:00:40,982
- Oh my? What's wrong with him?
- Idiot.

1573
01:00:40,982 --> 01:00:42,006
What's he even doing?

1574
01:00:42,006 --> 01:00:44,869
He's such an idiot. How can he be this silly?

1575
01:00:44,869 --> 01:00:47,560
He's using the circular motion?

1576
01:00:47,560 --> 01:00:48,739
He's shooting in a circle?

1577
01:00:48,739 --> 01:00:50,243
- Huh? He's backing up.
- Huh?

1578
01:00:50,243 --> 01:00:52,486
- He's going to wobble like that.
- Oh? He's coming in? He's coming in?

1579
01:00:52,486 --> 01:00:54,443
Oh! Hey...

1580
01:00:55,620 --> 01:00:58,398
- Isn't this it? "Bbo-pi Bbo-pi?" What is it?
- Yeah.

1581
01:00:58,398 --> 01:01:00,245
Isn't it "Bbo-pi Bbo?" Isn't this it?

1582
01:01:00,245 --> 01:01:03,084
[Flashy moves]
Oh! Hey...

1583
01:01:03,084 --> 01:01:04,972
- Isn't this it?
- Yeah, something like that...

1584
01:01:04,972 --> 01:01:06,610
- Whew, I'm tired.
- You're tired.

1585
01:01:06,610 --> 01:01:09,070
- Good job.
- Right.

1586
01:01:09,070 --> 01:01:10,595
- Thank you for your hard work.
- Yeah.

1587
01:01:10,595 --> 01:01:12,895
Whew, I'm exhausted... can I sit down too?

1588
01:01:12,895 --> 01:01:14,602
- Just a little bit...
- Eun Tak, come to the middle

1589
01:01:14,602 --> 01:01:16,382
so we can balance the weight.

1590
01:01:17,703 --> 01:01:20,143
- This isn't going to break, is it?
- Oh, my.

1591
01:01:20,143 --> 01:01:21,914
Are you getting nervous for no reason?

1592
01:01:25,305 --> 01:01:27,631
- Seriously, he's doing something weird again.
- Yeah.

1593
01:01:27,631 --> 01:01:29,656
- Shoot at it and see if it backs away.
- Huh?

1594
01:01:29,656 --> 01:01:31,419
- Shoot at it and see if it backs away.
- Bang!

1595
01:01:31,419 --> 01:01:33,282
[Charge! Charge!]

1596
01:01:33,282 --> 01:01:35,831
[Self-made sound effects]

1597
01:01:35,831 --> 01:01:38,281
- Oh, there it goes!
- Oh!

1598
01:01:38,281 --> 01:01:40,806
[The drone plays along
by making a dramatic escape]

1599
01:01:40,806 --> 01:01:43,820
Put on something thicker.

1600
01:01:43,820 --> 01:01:45,608
Aren't you cold?

1601
01:01:45,608 --> 01:01:48,545
- Are you cold?
- Why is she acting so tough?

1602
01:01:48,545 --> 01:01:51,435
- Since earlier, In Na...
- Touch me and see how warm I am.

1603
01:01:51,435 --> 01:01:53,293
- But you...
- I'm burning up.

1604
01:01:53,293 --> 01:01:56,610
- You get goosebumps every single time.
- Right.

1605
01:01:56,610 --> 01:01:59,356
My body itself is an extreme "F" type.

1606
01:01:59,356 --> 01:02:03,556
- The slightest thing gives me goosebumps.
- Oh...

1607
01:02:03,556 --> 01:02:05,572
- Come sit here.
- No, I'm okay.

1608
01:02:05,572 --> 01:02:08,629
- Sit on the swing.
- No, I'm so full that I'd rather stand.

1609
01:02:08,629 --> 01:02:09,922
Alright.

1610
01:02:09,922 --> 01:02:11,150
[Hmm...]

1611
01:02:11,150 --> 01:02:12,961
Oh, my legs... ugh...

1612
01:02:12,961 --> 01:02:15,660
[Standing up at the exact same time]

1613
01:02:17,061 --> 01:02:20,360
You wouldn't sit down
when I told you earlier, seriously...

1614
01:02:20,360 --> 01:02:21,455
[How to make two men give up
their seats at once]

1615
01:02:21,455 --> 01:02:24,482
This is funny. This is so funny.

1616
01:02:24,482 --> 01:02:25,696
You wouldn't sit when we told you to.

1617
01:02:25,696 --> 01:02:27,201
You wouldn't sit when we told you to,

1618
01:02:27,201 --> 01:02:28,593
and then you make people feel bad...

1619
01:02:28,593 --> 01:02:31,751
How was I supposed to know
I'd be standing this long?

1620
01:02:31,751 --> 01:02:32,796
"Oh, my legs."

1621
01:02:32,796 --> 01:02:35,460
[A max-level expert at handling
the Goblin and the Grim Reaper]

1622
01:02:35,460 --> 01:02:37,354
- Oh, my...
- The two of them got bounced right off.

1623
01:02:37,354 --> 01:02:38,616
That's hilarious.

1624
01:02:38,616 --> 01:02:41,294
[It's time for the final bucket-list item!]
- Let's go! - Let's go!

1625
01:02:41,294 --> 01:02:43,674
Let's hurry and go.

1626
01:02:43,674 --> 01:02:46,521
Don't run, don't run.

1627
01:02:46,521 --> 01:02:48,032
Let's push each other along like this.

1628
01:02:48,032 --> 01:02:51,013
Even just giving someone a little push uphill
makes it much easier.

1629
01:02:51,013 --> 01:02:53,528
[Helping each other up the steep hill]
- Gong Yoo, give In Na a push. - Gong Yoo.

1630
01:02:54,498 --> 01:02:55,870
No one's pushing me?

1631
01:02:55,870 --> 01:02:57,775
- Can't be helped.
- Can't be helped.

1632
01:02:57,775 --> 01:03:01,079
Ugh... actually, you're not
pushing me right now...

1633
01:03:01,079 --> 01:03:03,980
- You're leaning on me.
- Yeah, you...

1634
01:03:03,980 --> 01:03:05,311
In Na's dragging you along, Gong Yoo.

1635
01:03:05,311 --> 01:03:07,539
Yeah, I'm following her
with my hand on her shoulder.

1636
01:03:07,539 --> 01:03:09,830
[Where are they heading
while helping each other along?]

1637
01:03:09,830 --> 01:03:11,926
Oh, look over there, over there!

1638
01:03:12,774 --> 01:03:13,931
[Start]

1639
01:03:13,931 --> 01:03:16,032
- One, two, three.
<i>- Look your best!</i>

1640
01:03:16,032 --> 01:03:17,712
[Eun Tak and the Goblin
made memories through photos]

1641
01:03:17,712 --> 01:03:21,715
Wow, look at you smiling
even in all that chaos.

1642
01:03:21,715 --> 01:03:24,660
- I'm taking the picture.
- Come out.

1643
01:03:24,660 --> 01:03:30,400
[Even the three of them,
including the Grim Reaper, snap a photo]

1644
01:03:30,400 --> 01:03:33,814
[The final bucket-list item,
taking photos together]

1645
01:03:33,814 --> 01:03:36,472
First, you'll spend 40 minutes drawing
on the backdrop.

1646
01:03:36,472 --> 01:03:37,484
Oh.

1647
01:03:37,484 --> 01:03:38,723
Then you'll take your own photos
for 40 minutes.

1648
01:03:38,723 --> 01:03:39,602
Oh, okay.

1649
01:03:39,602 --> 01:03:42,190
We'll record the drawing
process as a time-lapse.

1650
01:03:42,190 --> 01:03:45,165
We'll also film you from behind
while you're drawing.

1651
01:03:45,165 --> 01:03:47,261
[From a hand-drawn backdrop
to a self-photo shoot]

1652
01:03:47,261 --> 01:03:49,444
Go ahead, you guys do it. I'll just watch.

1653
01:03:49,444 --> 01:03:52,707
You're just going to watch
while we do everything?

1654
01:03:52,707 --> 01:03:54,448
[Claiming the role of art supervisor]
- Go ahead. - Okay.

1655
01:03:54,448 --> 01:03:58,901
- Eun Tak, do this quickly, yeah.
- Wait... what did we even do?

1656
01:03:59,713 --> 01:04:06,535
[They made so many memories
over their two-day, one-night trip]

1657
01:04:07,566 --> 01:04:08,742
Nice to meet you.

1658
01:04:08,742 --> 01:04:10,045
What's with the sword?

1659
01:04:10,045 --> 01:04:11,260
Welcome!

1660
01:04:11,260 --> 01:04:12,736
[No wonder they're wondering
which memories to draw]

1661
01:04:12,736 --> 01:04:13,788
What did we do again?

1662
01:04:13,788 --> 01:04:15,793
- Oh, then...
- Yeah.

1663
01:04:15,793 --> 01:04:17,552
[The youngest comes up with an idea]
- Oh, then... - Yeah.

1664
01:04:17,552 --> 01:04:21,682
Then let's each pick a color...
and write "Go..."

1665
01:04:21,682 --> 01:04:26,009
- Should we just write "Goblin" like this?
- That's it?

1666
01:04:26,009 --> 01:04:27,233
Well...

1667
01:04:27,233 --> 01:04:30,304
[All their memories captured in "Goblin"]
we're not very good at drawing, so...

1668
01:04:30,304 --> 01:04:33,066
Or paint the whole background one color

1669
01:04:33,066 --> 01:04:34,844
and then put something on top?

1670
01:04:34,844 --> 01:04:37,198
Or should we make handprints?

1671
01:04:37,198 --> 01:04:40,120
We draw something
and stamp our four palms on it?

1672
01:04:40,120 --> 01:04:44,185
[Guys, here's the thing about art...]
- The thing about art is... - Yeah.

1673
01:04:45,392 --> 01:04:47,065
Which painting is better? This one or this one?

1674
01:04:47,065 --> 01:04:48,930
[The Goblin's 949 years of art wisdom shines?]
Get out.

1675
01:04:48,930 --> 01:04:50,300
Since this is a postmodernist piece...

1676
01:04:50,300 --> 01:04:51,360
This painting is titled

1677
01:04:51,360 --> 01:04:53,523
"The Defense of Captain Frans Banninck Cocq
and Lieutenant Willem van Ruytenburch."

1678
01:04:53,523 --> 01:04:56,144
Where would you hang this painting?

1679
01:04:56,144 --> 01:04:59,449
[Guys, here's the thing about art...]
- The thing about art is... - Yeah.

1680
01:04:59,449 --> 01:05:01,342
[Inaudible]
- Modern art doesn't work like that. - Oh...

1681
01:05:01,342 --> 01:05:03,099
You just go with the feeling.

1682
01:05:03,099 --> 01:05:05,456
- Draw whatever you want,
- Just do it.

1683
01:05:05,456 --> 01:05:07,270
then just come up with
a good interpretation afterward.

1684
01:05:07,270 --> 01:05:08,296
- Yeah, exactly.
- Right.

1685
01:05:08,296 --> 01:05:10,892
[End of the modern art lecture]
- That's modern art, yeah. - Right.

1686
01:05:11,736 --> 01:05:15,575
[Simply having fun]

1687
01:05:15,575 --> 01:05:17,467
- Eun Tak's doing everything.
- Yeah.

1688
01:05:17,467 --> 01:05:20,574
But if we write "Goblin" too plainly...

1689
01:05:20,574 --> 01:05:21,917
it'll be kind of boring.

1690
01:05:21,917 --> 01:05:23,068
Then what?

1691
01:05:23,068 --> 01:05:24,946
Let's make it a little playful
like putting the "Go" up there.

1692
01:05:24,946 --> 01:05:27,453
- Okay.
- Or put the "blin" down there.

1693
01:05:27,453 --> 01:05:30,326
Wow, this is my first time
painting with a roller.

1694
01:05:30,326 --> 01:05:32,808
- Wow, you can actually reach that?
- Yeah.

1695
01:05:32,808 --> 01:05:34,648
[Just as Dong Wook said,
Gong Yoo doesn't even need a ladder]

1696
01:05:34,648 --> 01:05:36,095
- The "lin."
- Huh?

1697
01:05:36,095 --> 01:05:38,612
How long is it going to take
to paint all of this?

1698
01:05:40,825 --> 01:05:44,180
How long am I supposed to paint all of this?

1699
01:05:44,180 --> 01:05:45,223
Why? What?

1700
01:05:45,223 --> 01:05:48,142
He's saying, "How long
am I supposed to paint this?"

1701
01:05:48,142 --> 01:05:51,482
[The grumbling Goblin is just too funny]
The Goblin keeps complaining.

1702
01:05:51,482 --> 01:05:54,413
- Oh? It looks pretty.
- Really? Should we stop? Is it done?

1703
01:05:54,413 --> 01:05:56,289
- "Goblin."
- Should we stop?

1704
01:05:56,289 --> 01:05:58,061
[If it looks nice, then stop there]

1705
01:05:58,061 --> 01:06:01,272
[Hard at work]

1706
01:06:01,272 --> 01:06:04,284
Just cover it with
whatever color you're drawn to.

1707
01:06:04,284 --> 01:06:06,204
Let's go abstract. Make it abstract.

1708
01:06:06,204 --> 01:06:09,880
- Something like this kind of brushstroke.
- Yeah...

1709
01:06:09,880 --> 01:06:11,162
[Brushstrokes flying toward "abstract art"]

1710
01:06:11,162 --> 01:06:13,749
- Something like this brushstroke.
- Yeah.

1711
01:06:14,560 --> 01:06:18,005
The number "1" looks so pretty!
Keep the colors like that.

1712
01:06:18,005 --> 01:06:19,663
- Really? Thanks.
- Yeah, let's do it that way.

1713
01:06:19,663 --> 01:06:22,497
- Yeah.
- Eun Tak, do the rest like that too.

1714
01:06:22,497 --> 01:06:25,545
- The "Goinbl..."
- It's "Goblin."

1715
01:06:25,545 --> 01:06:28,173
["Goblin" turned into "Goinbl"]
Do all the "Goinbl" like that.

1716
01:06:28,173 --> 01:06:31,823
- You arranged it so it reads "Goinbl."
- I said it's "Goinbl."

1717
01:06:31,823 --> 01:06:35,224
[The abstract artist offers an alternative]
Write the "bl" here in tiny letters.

1718
01:06:35,224 --> 01:06:37,497
Then what's "Goblinbl?"

1719
01:06:37,497 --> 01:06:39,377
[Cracking up]

1720
01:06:39,377 --> 01:06:41,870
No, I'm saying erase the "bl."

1721
01:06:42,970 --> 01:06:44,458
You idiots.

1722
01:06:44,458 --> 01:06:47,081
- Oh, it covers up.
- Yeah, it does.

1723
01:06:47,944 --> 01:06:48,987
The "bl."

1724
01:06:48,987 --> 01:06:51,317
[Fortunately, it's still fixable]

1725
01:06:51,317 --> 01:06:53,377
It's done, right?

1726
01:06:53,377 --> 01:06:56,120
[The abstract artist is satisfied]
Yeah, nice. It's much better than before.

1727
01:06:56,120 --> 01:06:59,243
- Yeah, it looks nice with the background.
- Yeah, you're right.

1728
01:07:01,644 --> 01:07:04,126
You two are basically the same,

1729
01:07:04,126 --> 01:07:07,882
but you keep saying
"this one's better" and "it's prettier."

1730
01:07:07,882 --> 01:07:11,879
- There you two go again.
- Still... we do have a good eye.

1731
01:07:12,597 --> 01:07:15,378
Oh! It looks nice.

1732
01:07:18,959 --> 01:07:21,794
[Kneeling...]

1733
01:07:21,794 --> 01:07:27,123
[The Goblin is pouring
his heart and soul into it]

1734
01:07:27,123 --> 01:07:29,651
Wow, Gong Yoo, this looks great.
The cloud effect is nice.

1735
01:07:29,651 --> 01:07:32,937
[This is supposed to be a cloud?]

1736
01:07:32,937 --> 01:07:35,298
Oh, it's like that. See? Look.

1737
01:07:35,298 --> 01:07:41,270
You know those ads planes
make in the sky overseas?

1738
01:07:41,270 --> 01:07:44,018
That's exactly it. Nice cloud effect.

1739
01:07:44,018 --> 01:07:45,113
Good, good, good.

1740
01:07:45,113 --> 01:07:49,086
- As expected, you really understood exactly...
- Yeah.

1741
01:07:49,086 --> 01:07:51,030
[The artist's intent understood]
what I was going for.

1742
01:07:51,030 --> 01:07:52,241
This is seriously no joke.

1743
01:07:52,241 --> 01:07:54,941
I just got goosebumps.

1744
01:07:54,941 --> 01:07:58,592
Go Eun Tak, come out for a moment.

1745
01:07:59,272 --> 01:08:00,976
[Splashing water]

1746
01:08:00,976 --> 01:08:02,466
- It's pretty.
- Yeah, yeah.

1747
01:08:02,466 --> 01:08:06,826
[The artistic activities become even bolder]
- Yeah, yeah. Good, good, good. - Oh...

1748
01:08:06,826 --> 01:08:09,335
[Completely absorbed]
Wow, this looks pretty.

1749
01:08:09,335 --> 01:08:12,440
- Yeah, it's good.
- Gong Yoo, are you relieving some stress?

1750
01:08:12,440 --> 01:08:15,445
[Stress being transformed into art]
- Are you relieving some stress? - Huh?

1751
01:08:17,309 --> 01:08:20,293
[Dong Wook joins in too]

1752
01:08:20,293 --> 01:08:21,708
- Oh, that one is pretty.
- Yeah.

1753
01:08:21,708 --> 01:08:23,970
[In Na really likes it]
- It looks kind of yellow. Nice. - Yeah.

1754
01:08:23,970 --> 01:08:25,381
Sprinkle it all over. Do it all.

1755
01:08:25,381 --> 01:08:29,277
[Everyone enters the world of art]
Yeah, let's sprinkle this. How do you do it?

1756
01:08:31,737 --> 01:08:34,564
[Lost in the moment]

1757
01:08:34,564 --> 01:08:36,849
- Ah, spraying it makes it easier.
- Yeah.

1758
01:08:36,849 --> 01:08:38,612
Should we do handprints now?

1759
01:08:38,612 --> 01:08:41,466
- Huh? Already?
- Already...

1760
01:08:41,466 --> 01:08:44,069
- Let's do more. This is fun.
- Seems like he doesn't want it to end.

1761
01:08:44,069 --> 01:08:45,620
This is fun.

1762
01:08:45,620 --> 01:08:49,728
[Dong Wook discovers his passion for art late]

1763
01:08:49,728 --> 01:08:51,073
You guys are ridiculous.

1764
01:08:51,073 --> 01:08:52,882
Please write all four of our names, Dong Wook.

1765
01:08:52,882 --> 01:08:54,001
- Okay.
- Anywhere you want.

1766
01:08:54,001 --> 01:08:56,303
- Roar.
- Oh, no!

1767
01:08:56,303 --> 01:08:57,906
Like this?

1768
01:08:59,327 --> 01:09:02,023
No, that's not it. That's not it.

1769
01:09:02,873 --> 01:09:05,653
Yay!

1770
01:09:05,653 --> 01:09:09,195
[Completely immersed in art]
[You too, In Na]

1771
01:09:09,195 --> 01:09:10,217
[Me too]

1772
01:09:10,217 --> 01:09:13,339
Wait a second. Dong Wook!
I'll at least do something like this.

1773
01:09:13,339 --> 01:09:15,488
No, no. Put it down. It's heavy.

1774
01:09:15,488 --> 01:09:17,141
It's not heavy at all.

1775
01:09:17,141 --> 01:09:20,063
[The Goblin is serious about joking around]
Go Eun, where should I write your name?

1776
01:09:20,063 --> 01:09:21,485
- Me?
- Yeah.

1777
01:09:21,485 --> 01:09:22,544
Just write it here.

1778
01:09:22,544 --> 01:09:25,054
- Here?
- Yeah.

1779
01:09:25,054 --> 01:09:26,078
Dong Wook.

1780
01:09:26,078 --> 01:09:29,718
[They say couples start to
resemble each other...]

1781
01:09:32,628 --> 01:09:35,903
- Little Gong Yoo, are you having fun?
- Yes!

1782
01:09:35,903 --> 01:09:38,381
[Little Gong Yoo leaves his footprints behind]
- See? - Little Go Eun.

1783
01:09:38,381 --> 01:09:42,219
Ah, so cute. Are those your feet?
Your feet are really small.

1784
01:09:42,219 --> 01:09:43,897
It's 170mm.

1785
01:09:43,897 --> 01:09:46,384
[Feet that somehow multiplied already]

1786
01:09:46,384 --> 01:09:49,519
- It's not human.
- The toes are spread out too much.

1787
01:09:49,519 --> 01:09:52,764
If you stamp six of them, it'll be awkward.

1788
01:09:52,764 --> 01:09:55,740
- Are you done? Can we take the photo now?
- Something is...

1789
01:09:55,740 --> 01:09:58,263
- Do you want to draw more?
- No.

1790
01:09:58,263 --> 01:09:59,452
All four of us,

1791
01:09:59,452 --> 01:10:02,990
- and this is the best we could do?
- Our drawing score is zero!

1792
01:10:02,990 --> 01:10:05,439
- It's a zero.
- This is the best four of us could do?

1793
01:10:05,439 --> 01:10:09,819
Now that I think about it...
Yoo In Na did nothing and only gave orders!

1794
01:10:09,819 --> 01:10:12,095
[a.k.a. The supervisor]

1795
01:10:12,095 --> 01:10:14,328
- I'll keep taking photos.
- Yeah.

1796
01:10:14,328 --> 01:10:17,581
[Time to take self photos now]

1797
01:10:17,581 --> 01:10:20,283
Shouldn't you lift one leg like this?

1798
01:10:20,283 --> 01:10:21,939
Like this?

1799
01:10:23,760 --> 01:10:28,335
[#Eyes_tightly_closed]
Seriously... look at the Grim Reaper.

1800
01:10:28,335 --> 01:10:31,232
Smile brightly. Hello!

1801
01:10:31,232 --> 01:10:33,485
Make a heart!

1802
01:10:34,211 --> 01:10:36,699
And next...

1803
01:10:36,699 --> 01:10:39,983
- It's time for the bbuing bbuing pose.
- No, don't do it. Don't do the bbuing bbuing.

1804
01:10:39,983 --> 01:10:42,478
Wait a second, I got dizzy
after sitting down and standing up.

1805
01:10:42,478 --> 01:10:43,545
Wait a second, oh...

1806
01:10:43,545 --> 01:10:45,732
Okay, it's the bbuing bbuing pose.

1807
01:10:45,732 --> 01:10:49,547
- Okay, everyone, bbuing bbuing.
- You two, stop fighting. Jeez...

1808
01:10:49,547 --> 01:10:52,329
[#We_are_close]

1809
01:10:52,329 --> 01:10:56,499
[#Cute_and_cool_again]

1810
01:10:56,499 --> 01:10:57,838
- Okay, this kind of thing is cute.
- Let's see.

1811
01:10:57,838 --> 01:10:59,318
- Ah, it's cute, it's cute.
- Wow!

1812
01:10:59,318 --> 01:11:00,864
[Satisfying photo shoot]
Ah, so cute, so cute.

1813
01:11:00,864 --> 01:11:02,886
- So cute.
- Yeah, cute. It's done.

1814
01:11:02,886 --> 01:11:04,496
- It came out.
- Just like this right now.

1815
01:11:04,496 --> 01:11:06,724
[#Us_just_like_this_now]

1816
01:11:08,755 --> 01:11:10,748
Why are we taking it like this?

1817
01:11:20,009 --> 01:11:24,925
[The memories of 1 night and 2 days
completed together]

1818
01:11:30,170 --> 01:11:33,405
It felt like we went back to
when we were young...

1819
01:11:33,405 --> 01:11:35,119
Every moment...

1820
01:11:35,119 --> 01:11:37,268
I truly think every moment
was really wonderful.

1821
01:11:37,268 --> 01:11:40,432
- It felt short! Time passed so quickly.
- Yeah, really, time...

1822
01:11:40,432 --> 01:11:43,430
In my opinion, Kim Go Eun
really hasn't changed at all.

1823
01:11:43,430 --> 01:11:44,679
- You too, Gong Yoo.
- Really?

1824
01:11:44,679 --> 01:11:45,822
But everyone is like that!

1825
01:11:45,822 --> 01:11:47,937
People don't really change. You know that.

1826
01:11:47,937 --> 01:11:51,809
- If you change... you die.
- What are you talking about?

1827
01:11:52,416 --> 01:11:55,458
I think everyone has just stayed
very consistent.

1828
01:11:55,458 --> 01:11:57,789
Not changing, staying the same...

1829
01:11:57,789 --> 01:11:59,236
in a good way.

1830
01:11:59,236 --> 01:12:02,048
The two-day trip feels a little... bittersweet?

1831
01:12:02,048 --> 01:12:03,907
- She'll contact me again.
- If I contact him...

1832
01:12:03,907 --> 01:12:05,726
- That's Kim Go Eun. She'll contact me.
- "Let's go."

1833
01:12:05,726 --> 01:12:08,486
- "Let's go."
- "Gong Yoo."

1834
01:12:08,486 --> 01:12:10,871
"Are you busy next year?"

1835
01:12:11,555 --> 01:12:13,720
Maybe she'll say,
"Should we go abroad this time?"

1836
01:12:13,720 --> 01:12:17,604
- "Let's go to Quebec." Something like that.
- I'm sure that could happen.

1837
01:12:18,293 --> 01:12:20,186
I told people around me,

1838
01:12:20,186 --> 01:12:24,098
"We're going on a trip
to celebrate Guardian's 10th anniversary,"

1839
01:12:24,098 --> 01:12:27,234
and the response I heard the most was
"Has it really already been 10 years?"

1840
01:12:27,234 --> 01:12:30,127
- Yeah, me too.
- That was the most common reaction.

1841
01:12:30,127 --> 01:12:31,924
Even now, people still...

1842
01:12:31,924 --> 01:12:36,634
seem to hold Guardian close to their hearts,

1843
01:12:36,634 --> 01:12:39,182
and we are very grateful for that as well.

1844
01:12:39,182 --> 01:12:42,300
- It's strangely touching.
- Yeah.

1845
01:12:42,300 --> 01:12:45,322
For continuing to love it
just as much as before,

1846
01:12:45,322 --> 01:12:47,231
we are so, so thankful.

1847
01:12:47,231 --> 01:12:52,133
To everyone who thinks of Guardian
whenever winter comes,

1848
01:12:52,133 --> 01:12:54,895
we sincerely thank you.

1849
01:12:54,895 --> 01:12:57,229
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1850
01:12:57,229 --> 01:13:00,626
Thank you for consistently
loving it for 10 years.

1851
01:13:00,626 --> 01:13:03,467
For 10th anniversary, 20th anniversary,
30th anniversary and beyond...

1852
01:13:03,467 --> 01:13:06,545
I hope it remains a masterpiece
that people remember forever.

1853
01:13:06,545 --> 01:13:09,009
I'll greet you again at the 20th anniversary.

1854
01:13:09,009 --> 01:13:11,589
Please continue to love it in the future.

1855
01:13:11,589 --> 01:13:15,814
Long live the immortal Guardian!

1856
01:13:15,814 --> 01:13:17,830
Like the drama is just about to begin...

1857
01:13:17,830 --> 01:13:19,680
should we say,
"Please continue to love Guardian?"

1858
01:13:19,680 --> 01:13:21,011
Yes, that sounds great.

1859
01:13:21,011 --> 01:13:24,286
- Please continue to love Guardian.
- Please continue to love Guardian.

1860
01:13:25,245 --> 01:13:27,795
- Shall we hold hands and go?
- Yeah.

1861
01:13:31,972 --> 01:13:33,934
We have to close the door.
